address: Jl. Menara, Pejaten, Langgardalem, Kec. Kota Kudus, Kabupaten Kudus, Jawa Tengah, Indonesia
name: Bagus S. Huda (Bagus)
text:
Historic mosques in Indonesia, is a form of acculturation of Javanese culture with Islam, especially the Aqsa Mosque, Palestine, in the form of 'Candi Bentar' and 'Menara Candi' in front of the azan tower and the location of 'kentongan' and dome forms and mosques similar to Al Aqsa Mosque.
Raden Ja'far Shodiq from Palestine was a cleric who was assigned to broadcast Islam in the area now called Kudus City, because of his love for his hometown, the first stone foundation was imported directly from Baitul Maqdis and the mosque's name and architectural style were likened to the Aqsa Mosque the name of this area is equated with the name of the mosque in his hometown, namely Al Quds and in the Javanese language called Kudus.
But not all are oriented towards Palestine as a hometown, he also acculturates with local culture, Hindu-Buddha. As stated on the inscription in the mosque's mihrab.
title: Masjid Al-Aqsha Menara Kudus

address: Jl. Menara, Pejaten, Langgardalem, Kec. Kota Kudus, Kabupaten Kudus, Jawa Tengah, Indonesia

One of the tourist object in Kudus. The tower is located right beside the mosque. You have to park your car elsewhere if you want to visit this place since it is not accessible by car.

Visited this place at around 8 pm and the tower looks nice with the lights and all. There are many stalls that offers souvenirs and also photographer service that will take your photo for a fee.

Was lucky to visit the Masjid on Friday. Masha Allah. So many people. It’s not just the artsy building but the history of Sunan Kudus. The Masjid is quite spacious. Well maintained. So many parking lot as much as the souvenirs shop 😂
The design! Enjoying the route to find women space. The signs are clear and readable! Visitors usually come to pray and visit Sunan’s tombstone which located just beside the Masjid. Walking around is kinda pleasant experience with clean areas toooo!

address: Jl. Menara, Pejaten, Langgardalem, Kec. Kota Kudus, Kabupaten Kudus, Jawa Tengah, Indonesia
name: Sofiyatun 2409
text:
Menara Kudus Mosque is one of the historical relics, as evidence of the spread of Islam in Java. This mosque is unique because of its building design, which is a combination of Hindu Culture and Islamic Culture.
Every day this place is always visited by pilgrims, pilgrims from around the Holy city usually visit on weekdays, Saturdays and Sundays are usually more visitors from outside the city. The 10th of Shura 'is the peak of the crowd at this mosque complex, in the framework of the death of Kanjeng Sunan Kudus
title: Masjid Al-Aqsha Menara Kudus

text:
The city of Demak holds great significance in the history of Islam's development in Indonesia. The Sunan Kalijaga Mosque stands as a testament to the peaceful spread of Islam, replacing previous religions in Java without conflict.

This mosque beautifully combines Javanese and Arab cultures, and despite being located in a tourist area, it still maintains a sense of reverence during worship.

text: Tempat ini adalah petilasan atau tempat yg dalam sejarah dijadikan tempat beribadah oleh sunan Bonang pada jamannya. Untuk lokasi mudah dijangkau karena ditepi jalan utama Pantura. Lokasi terawat bersih dan rapi. Mungkin hanya sekedar saran masukan saja, mohon ke depannya mungkin dibuat Pos informasi sehingga pengunjung dapat lebih faham apa saja isi dari lokasi. Di lokasi juga telah disediakan Kotak amal bagi pengunjung yg ingin beramal shadaqah, sehingga perlu koordinasi dgn dinas pariwisata untuk bisa merelokasi para pengemis yg bertebaran yg akan mempengaruhi citra dari lokasi. Terimakasih 🙏🙏🙏
textTranslated: This place is a petilasan or place that in history was used as a place of worship by Sunan Bonang in his time. The location is easy to reach because it is on the main Pantura road. The location is kept clean and tidy. Maybe it's just a suggestion, please make an information post in the future so that visitors can better understand what the location contains. A charity box has also been provided at the location for visitors who want to give charity, so it is necessary to coordinate with the tourism office to be able to relocate the scattered beggars who will affect the image of the location. Thank you 🙏🙏🙏
title: Pasujudan Sunan Bonang, Makam Putri Champa

address: 8FR9+369 Ex.Kadipaten, Bumi Jl. Binangun, Kebun, Bonang, Kec. Lasem, Kabupaten Rembang, Jawa Tengah 59271, Indonesia
name: Eka Rosyidda Anshori
text: Sunan Bonang merupakan salah satu wali songo yang ada di Jawa Timur. Tempatnya luas dan nyaman untuk peziarah. Memasuki area makam harus melepas alas kaki. Sebelum masuk makam ada kamar mandi yang cukup banyak di sebelah kanan area makam. Jika ke makan sunan bonang, bisa melewati gang kecil di samping masjid agung tuban. Area parkir kendaraan, untuk mobil atau elf dan kendaraan lainnya bisa parkir di area parkir pantai boom dan berjalan kaki ke makam sunan bonang. Sedangkan bagi bis ada terminal tersendiri serta memerlukan kendaraan lagi untuk ke makam sunan bonang, biasanya menaiki becak.
textTranslated: Sunan Bonang is one of the songo saints in East Java. The place is spacious and comfortable for pilgrims. Entering the tomb area requires removing footwear. Before entering the tomb, there are quite a few bathrooms to the right of the tomb area. If you are going to eat Sunan Bonang, you can go through the small alley next to the Tuban Grand Mosque. Vehicle parking area, for cars or elves and other vehicles, you can park in the Boom Beach parking area and walk to the Sunan Bonang grave. Meanwhile, for buses, there is a separate terminal and you need another vehicle to get to Sunan Bonang's grave, usually by trishaw.
title: Pasujudan Sunan Bonang, Makam Putri Champa

address: 8FR9+369 Ex.Kadipaten, Bumi Jl. Binangun, Kebun, Bonang, Kec. Lasem, Kabupaten Rembang, Jawa Tengah 59271, Indonesia
name: Diajeng Hastie
text: Entahlah mungkin ada saatnya ramai pengunjung sampai berdesakan dan ada kalanya sepi nyeyet bagai tidak terjamah manusia..... Atau mungkin ada misteri tersendiri, saya pun tidak paham. Saya termasuk orang awam dalam hal mistis.... Yang saya tau dari pandangan mata saya, dari bawah ya letaknya mudah dijangkau karena ada di pinggir jalan utama Surabaya-semarang, tersedia tempat parkir, toilet umum, mushola dan panjaja makanan. Naik ke atas melalui tanjakan tangga pastikan  kondisi fit dan istirahat dulu bila dirasa lelah di perjalanan naik ini. Sampai diatas ada lagi bangunan semacam aula yg bisa dipakai istirahat para pengunjung, ada mushola, tempat wudlu dan toilet cukup banyak, ada makam utama tempat peziarah berdo'a dan ada juga sekertariat... Pemandangan dari atas sini lumayan bagus dengan view pantai utara laut Jawa wilayah Rembang.
textTranslated: I don't know, maybe there are times when there are so many visitors that it's crowded and there are times when it's so quiet as if it hasn't been touched by humans... Or maybe there's a mystery of its own, I don't understand either. I am a layman when it comes to mystical matters.... What I know from my eyes is that from the bottom it is easy to reach because it is on the side of the main road Surabaya-Semarang, there is a parking lot, public toilets, prayer room and food stalls. Climb up via the stairs, make sure you are fit and rest first if you feel tired on the way up. Up to the top there is another hall-like building that can be used for visitors to rest, there is a prayer room, quite a lot of ablution places and toilets, there is a main grave where pilgrims pray and there is also a secretariat... The view from up here is quite good with a view of the north sea coast Java, Rembang region.
title: Pasujudan Sunan Bonang, Makam Putri Champa

text: Jika menaiki Bus maka parkiran dengan lokasi Makam sekitar 1,4km bisa ditempuh dengan dua jalur. Juga tersedia layanan jasa Becak dengan biaya 15k untuk 2-3 orang penumpang. Sesampainya di lokasi pengunjung melewati pasar sebelum ke makam dan saat memasuki gerbang makam maka ada beberapa orang yang akan menawarkan parfum kecil dengan embel-embel seikhlasnya, namun jika uang yang diberikan kurang dari 10k maka pengunjung akan didesak untuk membayar (hati-hati modus meminta minta bahkan penipuan). Sebelum ke arah makam ada Musholla yang lumayan luas dan kamar mandi/toilet yang cukup banyak. Memasuki makam, alas kaki dilepas dan dibawa.
textTranslated: If you take the bus, the parking lot with the grave location is around 1.4km and can be reached using two routes. Becak services are also available at a cost of 15k for 2-3 passengers. Arriving at the location, visitors pass through the market before going to the tomb and when they enter the tomb gate, there are several people who will offer small perfumes with frills as they please, but if the money given is less than 10k then visitors will be urged to pay (be careful with the begging mode even fraud). Before heading towards the tomb there is a prayer room which is quite large and there are quite a lot of bathrooms/toilets. Entering the tomb, footwear is removed and carried.
title: Pasujudan Sunan Bonang, Makam Putri Champa

address: 8FR9+369 Ex.Kadipaten, Bumi Jl. Binangun, Kebun, Bonang, Kec. Lasem, Kabupaten Rembang, Jawa Tengah 59271, Indonesia
name: Irfan Priyanto
text:
Pasujudan Sunan Bonang dan makam putri Cempo berada satu kompleks di atas gunung Lasem yang bisa dijangkau dari pesisir desa Bonang dengan menaiki tangga sekitar +- 150 meteran. Selain keduanya, ada juga makam jejeruk Sultan Mahmud sebelum menuju ke pasujudan. Waktu aku kesana malam jumat pas tengah malam, bisa berziarah dan berdoa dengan khusyuk di suasana yang tidak terlalu ramai dan sunyi.

Disana ada warung yang buka sampai tengah malam. Untuk menunya, kalau ingin makan malam lebih baik ke warung dekat parkiran saja karena warung di atas rata2 kalau tengah malam hanya mie instan dan serba minuman saja tanpa menu nasi. Tetapi disana ada kopi lasem juga.

Untuk kotak infaqnya disana lebih baik tidak banyak berpencar dan dijadiin satu saja. Selain itu keberadaan pengemis sebelum ke kompleks pasujudan itu menurutku agak mengganggu.
textTranslated:
Pasujudan Sunan Bonang and the tomb of Princess Cempo are in the same complex on Mount Lasem which can be reached from the coast of Bonang village by climbing stairs about +- 150 meters. Apart from these two, there is also the Jejeruk tomb of Sultan Mahmud before heading to Pasujudan. When I went there on a Friday night at midnight, I could make a pilgrimage and pray fervently in an atmosphere that was not too busy and quiet.

There is a shop there that is open until midnight. As for the menu, if you want to have dinner, it's better to go to the stall near the parking lot because the average stall at midnight is just instant noodles and drinks without a rice menu. But there is Lasem coffee there too.

For the infaq box there, it's better not to split it up too much and just make one. Apart from that, I think the presence of beggars before going to the Pasujudan complex is a bit disturbing.
title: Pasujudan Sunan Bonang, Makam Putri Champa

text:
Nyaman berada di sini. Pada Kamis sore lalu, masjid cukup ramai. Beberapa rombongan kecil silih berganti masuk keluar masjid untuk menunaikan sholat. Ada juga yang sedang melepas lelah dengan duduk santai di teras samping maupun serambi masjid.

Tempat wudhu pria berada di sebelah kanan, sedangkan bagi perempuan berada di sebelah kiri. Ada pembatas bagi jamaah yang akan masuk maupun keluar dari tempat wudhu. Di bagian dalam masjid, sudah diberi tanda untuk mengatur jamaah agar menjaga jarak. Bagian menarik dari masjid ini adalah atap masjid bersusun tiga yang melambangkan iman, islam, dan ikhsan (mohon koreksi jika keliru).
textTranslated:
It's comfortable to be here. On Thursday afternoon, the mosque was quite busy. Several small groups took turns going in and out of the mosque to perform prayers. There are also those who are unwinding by sitting relaxed on the side terrace or veranda of the mosque.

The ablution place for men is on the right, while for women it is on the left. There are barriers for pilgrims entering and leaving the ablution area. Inside the mosque, signs have been placed to direct the congregation to keep their distance. An interesting part of this mosque is the three-tiered mosque roof which symbolizes faith, Islam and Ikhsan (please correct me if this is wrong).
title: Masjid Sunan Kalijaga Kadilangu Demak

text: Pasujudan sunan bonang adalah salah satu tujuan wisata religi yang terletak ditepi jalan pantura daerah Rembang. Pasujudan sunan bonang adalah batu bekas tempat tahannuts (bersujud) sunan bonang. Ketika dimedio tahun 80'an pertama kali saya berkunjung, masih jelas terlihat bekas telapak tangan yang membentuk cekungan cekungan diatas bati tersebut, saat ini cekungan cekungan tersebut telah menjadi samar samar. Untuk mencapai pasujudan, pengunjung harus menaiki tangga yang lumayan tinggi. Diatas terdapat fasilitas yg cukup lengkap, ada banyak toilet yang bersih, musholla, joglo tempat istirahat serta warung warung makanan.
textTranslated: Pasujudan Sunan Bonang is a religious tourism destination located on the edge of the Pantura road in the Rembang area. Pasujudan Sunan Bonang is a stone used to hold nuts (prostrate) Sunan Bonang. When I first visited in the 80's, I could still clearly see the palm prints that formed the depressions above the bati, now the depressions have become faintly visible. To reach the pasujudan, visitors have to climb a fairly high ladder. Above there are quite complete facilities, there are lots of clean toilets, a prayer room, a joglo place to rest and food stalls.
title: Pasujudan Sunan Bonang, Makam Putri Champa

Pasujudan Sunan Bonang ( Lasem - Rembang )
Berada di atas bukit yang terletak di tepi pantai Binangun wilayah desa Bonang Kecamatan Lasem Kabupaten Rembang Provinsi Jawa Tengah. Kalau dari Arah Tuban ada di sebelah kiri jalan.
Pasujudan ini berada di  dalam sebuah cungkup yang di dalamnya di temukan empat buah batu. Batu yang terbesar di percaya sebagai pasujudan sunan bonang menunaikan ibadah
pada batu tempat salat ini terdapat bekas bekas anggota badan seperti lutut dan telapak tangan yang menunjukkan bekas orang sholat.

#jejakputulanang
textTranslated:
Pasujudan Sunan Bonang (Lasem - Rembang)
Located on a hill located on the edge of Binangun beach, Bonang village area, Lasem District, Rembang Regency, Central Java Province. If you are coming from Tuban, it is on the left side of the road.
This pasujudan is in a cupola in which four stones were found. The largest stone is believed to be the place where Sunan Bonang performs his worship
On the stone where you pray, there are traces of body parts such as knees and palms which indicate the marks of people praying.
There is also another cupola to the north of the Pasujudan Sunan Bonang cupola. It is believed by local residents to be the grave of Princess Cempo.

name: MUH JUNAEDI
text:
RATU KALINYAMAT

Ratu Kalinyamat (meninggal tahun 1579) adalah puteri raja Demak Trenggana yang menjadi bupati di Jepara. Ia terkenal di kalangan Portugis sebagai sosok wanita pemberani.

Nama asli Ratu Kalinyamat adalah Retna Kencana, puteri Sultan Trenggono, raja Demak (1521-1546). Pada usia remaja ia dinikahkan dengan Pangeran Kalinyamat.

Pangeran Kalinyamat berasal dari luar Jawa. Terdapat berbagai versi tentang asal-usulnya. Masyarakat Jepara menyebut nama aslinya adalah Win-tang, seorang saudagar Tiongkok yang mengalami kecelakaan di laut. Ia terdampar di pantai Jepara, dan kemudian berguru pada Sunan Kudus.

Versi lain mengatakan, Win-tang berasal dari Aceh. Nama aslinya adalah Pangeran Toyib, putera Sultan Mughayat Syah raja Aceh (1514-1528). Toyib berkelana ke Tiongkok dan menjadi anak angkat seorang menteri bernama Tjie Hwio Gwan. Nama Win-tang adalah ejaan Jawa untuk Tjie Bin Thang, yaitu nama baru Toyib.

Win-tang dan ayah angkatnya kemudian pindah ke Jawa. Di sana Win-tang mendirikan desa Kalinyamat yang saat ini berada di wilayah Kecamatan Kalinyamatan, sehingga ia pun dikenal dengan nama Pangeran Kalinyamat. Ia berhasil menikahi Retna Kencana putri bupati Jepara, sehingga istrinya itu kemudian dijuluki Ratu Kalinyamat. Sejak itu, Pangeran Kalinyamat menjadi anggota keluarga Kerajaan Demak dan memperoleh gelar Pangeran Hadiri.

Pangeran dan Ratu Kalinyamat memerintah bersama di Jepara. Tjie Hwio Gwan, sang ayah angkat, dijadikan patih bergelar Sungging Badar Duwung, yang juga mengajarkan seni ukir pada penduduk Jepara.
textTranslated:
QUEEN KALINYAMAT

Queen Kalinyamat (died 1579) was the daughter of the king of Demak Trenggana who became regent in Jepara. She is famous among the Portuguese as a brave woman.

Queen Kalinyamat's real name was Retna Kencana, daughter of Sultan Trenggono, king of Demak (1521-1546). When she was a teenager, she was married to Prince Kalinyamat.

Prince Kalinyamat came from outside Java. There are various versions about its origins. Jepara people say his real name is Win-tang, a Chinese merchant who had an accident at sea. He was stranded on the coast of Jepara, and then studied with Sunan Kudus.

Another version says that Win-tang comes from Aceh. His real name was Prince Toyib, son of Sultan Mughayat Syah, king of Aceh (1514-1528). Toyib traveled to China and became the adopted son of a minister named Tjie Hwio Gwan. The name Win-tang is the Javanese spelling of Tjie Bin Thang, which is Toyib's new name.

Win-tang and his adoptive father then moved to Java. There, Win-tang founded the village of Kalinyamat, which is currently in the Kalinyamatan District, so he was known as Prince Kalinyamat. He succeeded in marrying Retna Kencana, the daughter of the regent of Jepara, so that his wife was later nicknamed Queen Kalinyamat. Since then, Prince Kalinyamat became a member of the Demak Royal family and obtained the title Prince Hadiri.

Prince and Queen Kalinyamat ruled together in Jepara. Tjie Hwio Gwan, the adoptive father, was made governor with the title Sungging Badar Duwung, who also taught the art of carving to the people of Jepara.

name: Sahabat Inspirasi
text:
Menara Kudus Mosque was founded by Sunan Kudus. The holy minaret mosque was founded by Sunan Kudus in 1549 AD or in 956 Hijriyah. It is said that this building uses the Baitul Maqdis stone material from Palestine as the first stone. Menara Kudus Mosque is located in Kauman Village, Kota District, Kudus Regency, Central Java. This mosque is famously unique, because it is different from the others, why? Because this mosque has a tower similar to a temple building.
Therefore this mosque can remind us of the history of Islam's entry into the land of Java that cannot be separated from the role of Wali Sanga, especially Sunan Kudus. This Holy Mosque is a fusion of art between Islamic and Hindu culture. The establishment of the Menara Kudus Mosque is inseparable from the role of Sunan Kudus as its founder and initiator. Like the other saints, Sunan Kudus has a very wise way of preaching.
He is able to adapt and indigenize the teachings of Islam in the midst of a society that already has a culture as well as with the majority of Hindus and Buddhists. One of the mixture of Hindu and Buddhist culture in the preaching done by Sunan Kudus is that one of them can be seen in the above mosque image.
title: Masjid Al-Aqsha Menara Kudus

name: Ma'ruf Rifai
text: Pasujudan Sunan Bonang adalah wisata religi yang berada di desaBonang, Kecamatan Sluke, Kabupaten Rembang. Letaknya 17 km di sebelah timur kota Rembang jurusan Surabaya [1]. Sunan Bonang (Raden Maulana Makdum Ibrahim) meninggal tahun 1525 diusia 60 tahun. Tetapi, ada pendapat lain yang mengatakan, jika makam Sunan Bonang ada di wilayahTuban atau Madura, Jawa Timur. Tepatnya ada di depan pesisir Binangun. Jika hendak bepergian kesana, harus naik anak tangga terlebih dahulu, karena tempatnya sangat tinggi sekali. Pasujudan Sunan Bonang itu berwujud batu yang ada bekas sujudnyaSunan Bonang. Menurut cerita masyarakat disana, pasujudan Sunan Bonang zaman dahulu itu adalah batu yang digunakan sujudoleh Sunan Bonang untuk mendekatkan diri kepada Allah SWT. Sujudnya Sunan Bonangitu sangat lama sekali, sehingga batu tersebut membekaspalapannya Sunan Bonang. Sekarang Pasujudan Sunan Bonang tersebut dikeramatkan oleh masyarakat sekitar
textTranslated: Pasujudan Sunan Bonang is a religious tourist attraction that is located in Bonang village, Sluke District, Rembang Regency. It is located 17 km east of the city of Rembang in the direction of Surabaya [1]. Sunan Bonang (Raden Maulana Makdum Ibrahim) died in 1525 at the age of 60 years. However, there is another opinion that says that Sunan Bonang's grave is in the Tuban or Madura area, East Java. Precisely in front of the coast of Binangun. If you want to travel there, you have to climb the stairs first, because the place is very high. Sunan Bonang's prostration is in the form of a stone that bears the mark of Sunan Bonang's prostration. According to the stories of the people there, the pasujudan of Sunan Bonang in ancient times was the stone used to prostrate by Sunan Bonang to get closer to Allah SWT. Sunan Bonang's prostration took so long that the stone left Sunan Bonang's face. Now Pasujudan Sunan Bonang is sacred by the local community
title: Pasujudan Sunan Bonang, Makam Putri Champa

text:
makamnya ada di atas bukit, mirip seperti makam gunung pring, naik tangga lumayan tinggi. ada sekitar 100-200an anak tangga kalo ga salah ngitung, agak curam juga. tapi aman ada banyak tukang ojek bayarnya 10ribu sekali jalan. parkir mobil 10ribu juga.

sebelum naik ke makam bayar karcis dulu 2ribu per orang, sepanjang jalan tangga naik itu kanan kirinya banyak kios umkm jualan oleh-oleh, jajan, baju.

nah begitu sampe atas di pintu gerbang awal mau masuk area makam harus menitipkan alas kaki dulu di penitipan, nanti diambil pas waktu pulangnya (sambil ngisi kotak amal seikhlasnya untuk penitipan sandal). jadi di atas di area makam full telanjang kaki ya, bersih kok.

kalo dah menitipkan sandal bisa langsung ke meja registrasi dulu, mengisi buku tamu, dan shodaqoh seikhlasnya buat masuk makam. kemudian kalo dah dipersilakan masuk sama satpam/penjaganya maka kita baru masuk ke makam lewat beberapa gapura khas kerajaan gitu. pas sampe di atas bisa ngambil air minum dari gentong juga, tapi sayangnya agak kotor airnya.

untuk area dalam ruangan makamnya cukup sempit, dan beberapa pintu masuknya itu pendek banget jadi harus hati-hati kalo kepala terbentur. di dalam uangan makam alhamdulillah udah banyak kipas angin jadi ga panas.

oh ya di sini banyak banget petugas makamnya, mulai dari yang jaga penitipan sandal, meja registrasi, satpam yang mempersilakan masuk makam, dan beberapa petugas yang mengkondisikan para peziarah di dalam ruangan makam. mereka berpakaian beskap adat jawa gitu, mungkin karena makam ini juga masih cagar budaya milik keraton.

di area makam benar-benar bersih. nah tapi minusnya di masjid makam itu mukena nya ngga wangi, saran mungkin secara berkala dicek gitu kebersihan alat sholatnya rutin laundry
textTranslated:
The tomb is on a hill, similar to the Mount Pring tomb, up quite high stairs. There are around 100-200 steps, if I'm not mistaken, it's quite steep too. but it's safe, there are many motorbike taxi drivers who pay 10 thousand per way. 10 thousand car parking too.

Before going up to the tomb, pay a ticket first, 2 thousand per person. Along the way up the stairs, right and left, there are many small and medium-sized shops selling souvenirs, snacks and clothes.

So when you get to the top of the gate when you want to enter the tomb area, you have to leave your footwear in the safe first, then pick them up when you go home (while filling the charity box as sincerely as possible to keep your sandals). So upstairs in the grave area, you have bare feet, it's clean.

If you have left your sandals, you can go straight to the registration desk first, fill out the guest book, and pray as sincerely as possible to enter the tomb. Then, if we have been asked to enter by the security guard/guard, we will then enter the tomb through several typical royal gates. When you get to the top you can get drinking water from the barrel too, but unfortunately the water is a bit dirty.

The indoor area of ​​the tomb is quite narrow, and some of the entrances are very short so you have to be careful if you hit your head. Thank God there are lots of fans in the tomb so it doesn't get hot.

Oh yes, there are lots of cemetery staff here, starting from those guarding the sandals, the registration desk, the security guard who lets us in to the tomb, and several officers who condition the pilgrims in the tomb room. They are dressed in traditional Javanese beskap, perhaps because this tomb is still a cultural heritage property belonging to the palace.

the tomb area is really clean. well, but the minus in the graveyard mosque is that the mukenas don't smell good, a suggestion might be to check the cleanliness of the prayer tools regularly and wash them regularly.
title: Makam Sunan Bayat Ki Ageng Pandanaran

address: Mendin, Paseban, Bayat, Klaten Regency, Central Java 57462, Indonesia
name: Explore
text:
Sangat baik untuk refleksi diri.
Makam Sunan Pandanaran terletak di Kelurahan Paseban, Kecamatan Bayat, Klaten, tepatnya 15 kilometer sebelah tenggara dari pusat Kota Klaten. Makam ini juga memiliki banyak sebutan antara lain Makam Sunan Pandan Arang, Sunan Bayat atau Sunan Tembayat karena posisinya yang terletak di daerah Bayat.
Makamnya terletak di perbukitan ("Gunung Jabalkat") di wilayah Kecamatan Bayat, Klaten, Jawa Tengah, dan masih ramai diziarahi orang hingga sekarang. Dari sana pula konon ia menyebarkan ajaran Islam kepada masyarakat wilayah Mataram.

Tokoh ini hidup pada masa Kesultanan Demak (abad ke-15). Beliau juga dikenal sebagai wali pengganti Syekh Siti Jenar yang menurut kisah dihukum oleh Dewan Wali Sanga
textTranslated:
Very good for self-reflection.
Sunan Pandanaran's tomb is located in Paseban Village, Bayat Subdistrict, Klaten, exactly 15 kilometers southeast from the center of Klaten City. This tomb also has many names, including the Tomb of Sunan Pandan Arang, Sunan Bayat or Sunan Tembayat because of its position in the Bayat area.
His tomb is located in the hills ("Mount Jabalkat") in the region of Bayat District, Klaten, Central Java, and is still visited by many people until now. From there he is said to have spread the teachings of Islam to the people of the Mataram region.

This figure lived during the Demak Sultanate (15th century). He is also known as the successor guardian of Sheikh Siti Jenar who according to the story was punished by the Dewan Wali Sanga
title: Makam Sunan Bayat Ki Ageng Pandanaran

address: Mendin, Paseban, Bayat, Klaten Regency, Central Java 57462, Indonesia
name: Hanif Tasya Revv
text:
Sengaja berangkat ziarah lebih pagi karena nggak mau tempuk sama peziarah lainnya, Tapi jadi agak jengkel dengan peziarah lainnya yang maksa masuk ke makam Sunan Pandanaran, padahal disitu masih ada aku dan adik aku yang masih fokus ziarah. Sebelum aku masuk pun, aku antri karena di dalam makam masih ada orang ziarah juga (karena takut ganggu).
Setelah aku masuk, bbrp menit menjelang akhir doa ada serombongan peziarah yg maksa masuk banget langsung duduk di depan tempat aku dan adikku duduk. Setelah selesai pun mau keluar gabisa, karena pintu makam untuk keluar/masuk orang di duduki peziarah tersebut full.
Menurutku pelayanannya sudah baik bagus, dan sewajarnya.
Mungkin sarannya aja untuk peziarah lainnya, agar tetap menunggu antrian sebelumnya selesai dan keluar dari makam, mengingat makam inti sunan Pandanaran tidak cukup luas
textTranslated:
I deliberately went on the pilgrimage early because I didn't want to bump into other pilgrims, but I was a bit annoyed with the other pilgrims who insisted on going to Sunan Pandanaran's grave, even though there were still me and my sister there who were still focused on the pilgrimage. Before I entered, I queued because there were still people visiting the tomb (for fear of disturbing them).
After I entered, a few minutes before the end of the prayer there was a group of pilgrims who forced their way in and immediately sat in front of where my sister and I were sitting. After finishing, I couldn't go out, because the door to the tomb for pilgrims to enter/exit was full.
I think the service is good and reasonable.
Maybe just a suggestion for other pilgrims, to keep waiting for the previous queue to finish and leave the tomb, considering that the main tomb of Sunan Pandanaran is not large enough

text:
Makam Ratu Kalinyamat di Mantingan Jepara, di dalam cungkup besar bersama makam suaminya, yaitu Pangeran Hadlirin, serta sejumlah kerabat. Kompleks makam di belakang Masjid Astana Mantingan itu cukup luas, dan di luar tembok ada kompleks pemakaman umum.

Jalan dari halaman masjid ke gerbang makam agak melengkung, dan di kiri terlihat akses masuk dari selatan dengan melewati gapura bertulis syahadat yang dipindahkan dari jalan raya. Area di dalam kompleks masjid dan makam kondisinya terlihat baik.
textTranslated:
Queen Kalinyamat's grave in Mantingan Jepara, in a large cupola along with the grave of her husband, Prince Hadlirin, and a number of relatives. The tomb complex behind the Astana Mantingan Mosque is quite large, and outside the walls there is a public burial complex.

The road from the mosque yard to the tomb gate is slightly curved, and on the left you can see the entrance from the south by passing through the gate with the shahada inscribed on it which was moved from the main road. The areas inside the mosque complex and the cemetery appear to be in good condition.
title: Tomb of Queen Kalinyamat

name: Carubanan
street: 4J2W+7CF, Depan masjid dan makam sunan Kalijaga
text:
Nyaris ada yang terlewatkan dari pengamatan, ketika kita berusaha mencoba melacak dan menginventarisasi masjid-masjid bersejarah yang sangat berperan dalam penyebaran dan pengembangan agama Islam di Tanah Air, yakni keberadaan Masjid Sunan Kalijaga di Kadilangu, Kabupaten Demak, Jawa Tengah.

Memang, keberadaan bangunan suci yang satu ini seperti tenggelam oleh nama besar Masjid Agung Demak, sehingga jarang dibicarakan dalam sejarah. Tetapi, kalau kita amati dan cermati dari prasasti yang ada, peran masjid ini dalam penyebaran dan pengembangan agama Islam, terutama di tanah Jawa, tidak kalah pentingnya dibandingkan dengan masjid-masjid bersejarah lainnya.

Masjid Sunan Kalijaga lokasinya berada di Desa Kadilangu, Demak, hanya beberapa meter di sebelah timur Kompleks Makam Sunan Kalijaga dan keluarganya di Kadilangu—makam istri dan ayahnya (Raden Wilotikto).

Tidak diketahui secara pasti tanggal dan tahun pendirian masjid kuno ini, termasuk tokoh yang mendirikannya. Tetapi, dari prasasti yang ada dan tersimpan di masjid, diketahui bahwa Masjid Sunan Kalijaga direnovasi pertama kali pada tahun 1564 M oleh Pangeran Wijil.

Hanya saja Pangeran Wijil yang mana yang dimaksud, karena dalam sejarah dikenal ada lima orang Pangeran Wijil dari I sampai V. Semuanya merupakan penerus Sunan Kalijaga di daerah Kadilangu dan sekitarnya. Yang menarik dari sumber keyakinan masyarakat Kadilangu dan sekitarnya bahwa Masjid Sunan Kalijaga semula adalah langgar (surau/ mushala) yang dibuat oleh Sunan Kalijaga sebelum ia mendirikan Masjid agung Demak.

Menurut cerita orang tua terdahulu, diyakini bahwa cikal bakal berdirinya bangunan Masjid Agung Demak diilhami bangunan langgar ini. Masjid Sunan Kalijaga ini lebih dahulu berdiri daripada Masjid Agung Demak. Baru pada zaman Pangeran Wijil, langgar Sunan Kalijaga itu dikembangkan menjadi sebuah masjid karena tuntutan jumlah jamaah. Sejak berdirinya hingga sekarang, masjid dengan bangunan induk yang asli berukuran 10 x 16 m ini telah mengalami beberapa kali perubahan dan perbaikan pada pemugaran karena tuntutan zaman dan jumlah jamaah yang semakin membludak. Perbaikan yang dilakukan secara besar-besaran dilakukan pada tahun 1970 dengan menambah beberapa bangunan serambi yang cukup luas.

Meski telah beberapa kali mengalami perbaikan, namun bangunan induk yang asli tidak pernah diubah, masih tetap dipertahankan keasliannya. Lebih-lebih keberadaan keempat tiang penyangga utama bangunan (sokoguru) yang oleh masyarakat setempat masih dikeramatkan dan masih berdiri kokoh menjadi saksi sejarah perkembangan Islam di Kadilangu dan sekitarnya. Keempat sokoguru itu terbuat dari kayu jati pilihan.

Pada tahun 1990, pengurus Masjid Sunan Kalijaga kembali melakukan pembangunan fisik meliputi tempat shalat dan tempat wudhu putri yang terpisah dengan pria.

Masjid ini berdiri di tengah-tengah masyarakat santri dan sudah tentu syiar masjid ini sangat membanggakan. Ini terlihat dari kegiatan pengajian yang marak di masjid ini. Juga pendidikan Madrasah Diniyah dan TPA tidak ketinggalan melengkapi kemakmuran masjid “langgar”nya Sunan Kalijaga ini.
textTranslated:
There is almost something that is missed from observation, when we try to track and inventory historical mosques that played a big role in the spread and development of Islam in the country, namely the existence of the Sunan Kalijaga Mosque in Kadilangu, Demak Regency, Central Java.

Indeed, the existence of this sacred building seems to be drowned out by the great name of the Great Mosque of Demak, so it is rarely discussed in history. However, if we observe and look carefully at the existing inscriptions, the role of this mosque in the spread and development of Islam, especially in Java, is no less important than other historical mosques.

The Sunan Kalijaga Mosque is located in Kadilangu Village, Demak, just a few meters east of the Tomb Complex of Sunan Kalijaga and his family in Kadilangu—the graves of his wife and father (Raden Wilotikto).

It is not known for certain the date and year this ancient mosque was founded, including the figure who founded it. However, from the existing inscriptions stored in the mosque, it is known that the Sunan Kalijaga Mosque was first renovated in 1564 AD by Prince Wijil.

It's just which Prince Wijil is meant, because in history it is known that there were five Prince Wijil from I to V. All of them were the successors of Sunan Kalijaga in the Kadilangu area and its surroundings. What is interesting from the sources of belief among the people of Kadilangu and its surroundings is that the Sunan Kalijaga Mosque was originally a langgar (surau/mushala) made by Sunan Kalijaga before he founded the Grand Mosque of Demak.

According to stories from previous parents, it is believed that the origin of the Great Mosque of Demak was inspired by this broken building. The Sunan Kalijaga Mosque was founded earlier than the Great Mosque of Demak. It was only during the time of Prince Wijil that the Sunan Kalijaga langgar was developed into a mosque due to the demands of the number of worshipers. Since its founding until now, the mosque with its original main building measuring 10 x 16 m has undergone several changes and restoration improvements due to the demands of the times and the increasing number of worshipers. Major repairs were carried out in 1970 by adding several large porches.

Even though it has undergone several repairs, the original main building has never been changed, its authenticity is still maintained. Moreover, the existence of the four main supporting pillars of the building (sokoguru) which the local community still holds sacred and still stands firmly is a witness to the history of the development of Islam in Kadilangu and its surroundings. The four pillars are made from selected teak wood.

In 1990, the management of the Sunan Kalijaga Mosque carried out physical construction again, including a prayer area and a place for women's ablutions which were separate from men's.

This mosque stands in the midst of the Islamic boarding school community and of course the publicity of this mosque is very proud. This can be seen from the recitation activities that are widespread in this mosque. Also Madrasah Diniyah and TPA education are not left behind in complementing the prosperity of Sunan Kalijaga's "violating" mosque.

Here there are around 250 steps (meaning if PP goes up and down ± 500 steps). That's not bad, it's a sport, hehe. But if you don't feel up to it, that's okay, there are many motorbike taxi services available below, via another road that goes straight to the top. The cost is not expensive, around 7000. text: Baru pertama kali berkunjung ke makam ki ageng pandanaran, itupun dalam rangka ziarah HUT Kab. Boyolali ke 171. Lokasinya di Bayat, Klaten. Jalan menuju kesana sudah bagus dan mudah diakses. Menuju ke makam, jalan sangat menanjak tp sudah ada tangga2 dan naungan. Untuk yang tidak kuat jalan nanjak, tersedia tukang ojek yang akan mengantar langsung ke makam. Suasana sangat tenang ketika sampai makam.
textTranslated: This was the first time I visited Ki Ageng Pandanaran's grave, and that too as part of the Kab.'s anniversary pilgrimage. Boyolali to 171. The location is in Bayat, Klaten. The road to get there is good and easy to access. Upon arrival, visitors are greeted by various pilgrimage knick-knack traders, there are art market facilities and a pavilion before entering the tomb area. To get to the tomb, the road is very uphill but there are stairs and shade. For those who cannot walk uphill, there are motorbike taxi drivers who will take you directly to the grave. The atmosphere was very calm when we arrived at the grave.
title: Makam Sunan Bayat Ki Ageng Pandanaran

Thank God I often visit SuNan Bayat's grave. Coincidentally the distance is not too far. Still can be reached by motorbike from Solo.

😊

textTranslated: There was something interesting about this place 5 years ago, when we didn't have any children... there was one person who actually recommended taking noni fruit in the area of ​​Sunan Kalijaga's grave for husband and wife to eat, so ask Mbah Sunan's wasilah to give him children... ask the guard to get it later😊 😊 Thank God I now have two children.

text:
Saya bangga terhadap masyarakat & Pemda setempat yg melindungi, merawat peninggalan sunan Kalijaga termasuk makkam beliau.
Saya KECEWA😱😱 kepada pemda& pengelola tentang rumah makan di sekitarnya yang seolah-olah menjebak penjiarah dgn harga yg tinggi.
Sekedar saran untuk Pemda setempat.
Bok ya di sarankan untuk membuat daftar harga makanan (wajib) terserah mau di kasih harga tinggi/murah yg penting Sama-sama tahu&sama menghitung. kasihan penjiarah yang rata rata dari rakyat kebawah yg bawa uang jajan pas Pasan.
Terimakasih
textTranslated:
I am proud of the local community & government for protecting and caring for Sunan Kalijaga's heritage, including his grave.
I am DISAPPOINTED😱😱 with the local government & management about the surrounding restaurants which seem to be trapping pilgrims with high prices.
Just a suggestion for the local government.
OK, it's recommended that you make a list of food prices (mandatory). It's up to you whether you want to give a high/low price. The important thing is that you both know & count together. I feel sorry for the average pilgrim from the lower classes who brings pocket money just barely.
Thank You

text: Masjid bersejarah yang menjadi cikal bakal kota demak. Gag terasa sudah 23 tahun berziarah ke makam sunan kalijaga, salah satu sunan besar dalam sejarah yang menjadi peletak dasar sinkronisasi agama dengan budaya jawa. Masjid masih terjaga keasliannya dengan tambahan peneduh yang bisa menambah jumlah jemaah yang sedang melaksanakan sholat jumat
textTranslated: The historic mosque which is the forerunner of the city of Demak. I can't believe it's been 23 years since I've been on a pilgrimage to the grave of Sunan Kalijaga, one of the great Sunans in history who laid the foundation for synchronizing religion with Javanese culture. The mosque still maintains its authenticity with additional shade which can increase the number of congregants performing Friday prayers

textTranslated:
This pilgrimage place is very busy with pilgrims from various cities.
But there is something very unfortunate about this place. The tomb seems to be used as an object for making money by the management who requires reporting.
And if you don't want to report, you will be shouted at with harsh words which are very inappropriate for religious tourism.
I have also eaten at rice stalls in this area and found the prices to be expensive. The taste was very disappointing.
This place has 2 entrances which are inversely proportional to the price of the food.
If you enter from the front door of the cemetery there are lots of food stalls which are disappointing. But in my experience entering from the side door near the mosque there are generally friendly prices.

text:
makam putri cempo dan tempat pasujudan sunan bonang
lokasinya tepat di pinggir jalan raya pantura.
terdapat banyak warung yang menyediakan oleholeh khas dan makanan.
menjadi lokasi tepat buat traveler religi atau yang cuma sekedar lewat jalur pantura.
ada mushala meski kecil tapi airnya melimpah...

textTranslated:
Putri Cempo's tomb and Sunan Bonang's place of worship
The location is right on the edge of the Pantura highway.
There are many stalls providing typical souvenirs and food.
It is the right location for religious travelers or those just passing through the Pantura route.
There is a prayer room, although it is small, but the water is abundant...
the location is a bit far with an uphill track
title: Pasujudan Sunan Bonang, Makam Putri Champa

address: 8FR9+369 Ex.Kadipaten, Bumi Jl. Binangun, Kebun, Bonang, Kec. Lasem, Kabupaten Rembang, Jawa Tengah 59271, Indonesia
name: Indra Susandi
text: Lokasinya berada di pinggir jalan raya Pantura. Dipinggir jalan langsung parkir. Untuk ke lokasi harus naik banyak anak tangga. Banyak pengemisnya yang keliatan masih muda2 dan kuat. Di gerbang atas jg ada pengemis. Kotak amal jg bnyk. Di ruang pasujudan terlihat 4 batu dan salah satunya ada bekas tapak Sunan Bonang. Di atas batu juga ada kota amal... sebaiknya disingkirkan aja taruh diluar. Ada juga bangunan khusus utk makan Putri Campa salah seorang murid Sunan Bonang
textTranslated: The location is on the edge of Pantura road. Direct parking on the side of the road. To get to the location you have to climb a lot of stairs. Many beggars who look young and strong. There are also beggars at the top gate. There are also many charity boxes. In the prayer room you can see 4 stones and one of them is the former site of Sunan Bonang. There is also a city of charity on the rock... it's best to remove it and put it outside. There is also a special building for eating Putri Campa, one of Sunan Bonang's students
title: Pasujudan Sunan Bonang, Makam Putri Champa

text: Salah satu tempat petilasan wali dalam berdakwah menyebarkan agama islam di tanah jawa, khususnya daerah rembang,  nuansa religius masih terasa,  beberapa peninggalan kanjeng Sunan Bonang masih terawat dengan baik,  bukan berarti mengkultuskan peninggalan sunan, bagi para peziarah harus tetap berpegang pada agama yang diyakini,  jangan sampai melakukan hal yang bisa menjurus pada perbuatan syirik karena itu dosa besar yang tidak dikehendaki oleh Sang Maha Pencipta...
textTranslated: One of the places where the saints used to preach to spread Islam in Java, especially the Rembang area, the religious nuance is still felt, some of the relics of Kanjeng Sunan Bonang are still well maintained, this does not mean cultivating Sunan relics, pilgrims must stick to the religion they believe in, Don't do things that can lead to shirk because that is a big sin that is not desired by the Almighty Creator...

name: Ali Munir (Alam Endah)
text:
Pasujudan Sunan Bonang, merupakan salah satu lokasi wisata religi yang terdapat di Kecamatan lasem, kabupaten Rembang. Lokasinya berada tepat di sisi Jalan Raya Pantura, beberapa kilometer ke utara kota Lasem.

Konon, di bukit yang berada di bibir pantai Laut Jawa inilah Sunan Bonang pernah tinggal, melakukan .ibadah mendekatkan diri kepada Allah. Di tempat ini terdapat batu yang dipercaya sebagai tempat berpijak Sunan Bonang.
textTranslated:
Pasujudan Sunan Bonang, is one of the religious tourism locations in Lasem District, Rembang Regency. The location is right on the side of Jalan Raya Pantura, a few kilometers north of the city of Lasem.

It is said that it was on this hill on the shoreline of the Java Sea that Sunan Bonang once lived, performing worship to get closer to Allah. In this place there is a stone which is believed to be the foothold of Sunan Bonang.
title: Pasujudan Sunan Bonang, Makam Putri Champa

textTranslated: The Tembayat Tomb Complex is a living monument, meaning that it is still used today as a place of pilgrimage and burial, especially for the Sunan Bayat breed. Pesarean, which is on top of a hill, is a special experience for pilgrims when they get there.

Almost every year we always make a pilgrimage to his grave.

name: zainal abidin
text: Sunan Bayat atau juga Sunan Pandanaran adalah sosok besar dalam sejarah penyebaran agama Islam terutama di kawasan Jawa Tengah. Sosok yang hidup di masa yang sama dengan Wali Sanga ini berjuang selama 25 tahun untuk menyebarkan agama bersama sahabat dan pengikutnya dari kawasan Bayat, Klaten. Di Bayat pula Sunan dimakamkan dan di sana pula kemudian sebuah kompleks pemakaman megah dibangun untuk mengenang jasa-jasanya. Sosok besar nyaris tidak pernah luput dengan cerita-cerita besar yang muncul selama hidup mereka, termasuk di diri Sunan Pandanaran, baik selama dia hidup bahkan setelah wafatnya.
textTranslated: Sunan Bayat or also Sunan Pandanaran is a major figure in the history of the spread of Islam, especially in the Central Java region. This figure who lived at the same time as Wali Sanga struggled for 25 years to spread religion with his friends and followers from the Bayat area, Klaten. It was also in Bayat that Sunan was buried and there a magnificent burial complex was built to commemorate his services. Great figures almost never escape the big stories that emerge during their lives, including Sunan Pandanaran, both during his life and even after his death.
title: Makam Sunan Bayat Ki Ageng Pandanaran

text:
Di Makam Sunan padanaran bernama ini awalnya  bernama Hastana Cakra Kembang , memiliki beberapa gerbang dan bangunan yang perlu dilalui peziarah.

Gapura Segara Muncar ini dibuat dari batu alam, merupakan gapura pertama yang terletak di terminal Paseban. Pada kaki gapura sebelah barat terdapat tulisan candra sengkala yang bunyinya Murti Sarira Jleging Ratu yang artinya 1488 dan merupakan tahun berdirinya gapura tersebut.
textTranslated:
The Sunan Padanaran Tomb, originally called Hastana Cakra Kembang, has several gates and buildings that pilgrims need to pass through.

The Segara Muncar Gate, made from natural stone, is the first gate located at the Paseban terminal. At the foot of the western gate there is an inscription candra sengkala which reads Murti Sarira Jleging Ratu which means 1488 and is the year the gate was founded.

text:
Makam Sunan Pandanaran atau biasa dikenal dengan sebutan Sunan Bayat (Tembayat) ini terletak di Desa Paseban, Kecamatan Bayat, Kabupaten Klaten. Menurut keterangan penduduk setempat, makam ini dibangun pada 1526 Masehi.

Makam ini merupakan salah satu wisata religi yang berada di wilayah Kabupaten Klaten. Almarhum Sunan Bayat sebelum menjadi salah satu pensyiar Agama Islam pernah menjabat sebagai Bupati Semarang yang saat itu  menjadi bagian dari Kesultanan Demak. Beliau sebelumnya bergelar Ki Ageng Pandanaran II (putera dari Ki Ageng Pandanaran I yang merupakan Bupati Semarang pertama).

Setelah menjadi murid Sunan Kalijaga, Beliau meninggalkan harta dan tahtanya untuk kemudian bersama isterinya melakukan syiar hingga ke wilayah Klaten. Dalam perjalanannya, banyak peristiwa-peristiwa yang jejaknya masih tertinggal hingga sekarang berupa penamaan wilayah seperti Salatiga dan Boyolali.

Kompleks Makam Sunan Pandanaran menempati sebuah bukit dengan makam umum di bagian dasar dan kompleks makam utama berada di puncak bukit.

Catatan:

1. Situs ini dikelola oleh Pemerintah Desa setempat.
2. Siapkan fisik, karena Makam Sunan Pandanaran ini terletak di atas bukit sehingga kita harus menapaki anak tangga yang jumlahnya ratusan untuk menuju kesana.
3. Disebelah kanan dan kiri tangga banyak terdapat kios-kios yang menawarkan oleh-oleh.
4. Tiket Masuk : Rp 1.000,-/orang
5. Parkir Motor : Rp 3.000,-
6. Parkir Mobil : Rp 5.000,-
7. Parkir Bus : Rp 10.000,-
8. Kotak Amal : seikhlasnya
9. Harga makanan di warung-warung di tempat parkir sangat terjangkau dan pelayanannya ramah, jangan lupa ucapkan terimakasih setelah membayar.
textTranslated:
The tomb of Sunan Pandanaran or commonly known as Sunan Bayat (Tembayat) is located in Paseban Village, Bayat District, Klaten Regency. According to local residents, this tomb was built in 1526 AD.

This tomb is one of the religious tourist attractions in the Klaten Regency area. The late Sunan Bayat, before becoming a broadcaster of Islam, served as Regent of Semarang, which at that time was part of the Demak Sultanate. He previously had the title Ki Ageng Pandanaran II (son of Ki Ageng Pandanaran I who was the first Regent of Semarang).

After becoming a student of Sunan Kalijaga, he left his wealth and throne and then together with his wife carried out preaching to the Klaten area. Along the way, there were many events whose traces still remain today in the form of the naming of areas such as Salatiga and Boyolali.

The Sunan Pandanaran Tomb Complex occupies a hill with a public tomb at the base and the main tomb complex at the top of the hill.

Notes:

1. This site is managed by the local Village Government.
2. Prepare physically, because the Tomb of Sunan Pandanaran is located on a hill so we have to climb hundreds of steps to get there.
3. To the right and left of the stairs there are many stalls offering souvenirs.
4. Entrance ticket: IDR 1,000/person
5. Motorbike Parking: IDR 3,000,-
6. Car Parking: IDR 5,000,-
7. Bus Parking: IDR 10,000,-
8. Charity Box: as sincere as possible
9. The price of food at the stalls in the parking lot is very affordable and the service is friendly, don't forget to say thank you after paying.
title: Makam Sunan Bayat Ki Ageng Pandanaran

text:
Nyaris ada yang terlewatkan dari pengamatan, ketika kita berusaha mencoba melacak dan menginventarisasi masjid-masjid bersejarah yang sangat berperan dalam penyebaran dan pengembangan agama Islam di Tanah Air, yakni keberadaan Masjid Sunan Kalijaga di Kadilangu, Kabupaten Demak, Jawa Tengah.

Memang, keberadaan bangunan suci yang satu ini seperti tenggelam oleh nama besar Masjid Agung Demak, sehingga jarang dibicarakan dalam sejarah. Tetapi, kalau kita amati dan cermati dari prasasti yang ada, peran masjid ini dalam penyebaran dan pengembangan agama Islam, terutama di tanah Jawa, tidak kalah pentingnya dibandingkan dengan masjid-masjid bersejarah lainnya.

Masjid Sunan Kalijaga lokasinya berada di Desa Kadilangu, Demak, hanya beberapa meter di sebelah timur Kompleks Makam Sunan Kalijaga dan keluarganya di Kadilangu—makam istri dan ayahnya (Raden Wilotikto).

Tidak diketahui secara pasti tanggal dan tahun pendirian masjid kuno ini, termasuk tokoh yang mendirikannya. Tetapi, dari prasasti yang ada dan tersimpan di masjid, diketahui bahwa Masjid Sunan Kalijaga direnovasi pertama kali pada tahun 1564 M oleh Pangeran Wijil.

Hanya saja Pangeran Wijil yang mana yang dimaksud, karena dalam sejarah dikenal ada lima orang Pangeran Wijil dari I sampai V. Semuanya merupakan penerus Sunan Kalijaga di daerah Kadilangu dan sekitarnya. Yang menarik dari sumber keyakinan masyarakat Kadilangu dan sekitarnya bahwa Masjid Sunan Kalijaga semula adalah langgar (surau/ mushala) yang dibuat oleh Sunan Kalijaga sebelum ia mendirikan Masjid agung Demak.

Menurut cerita orang tua terdahulu, diyakini bahwa cikal bakal berdirinya bangunan Masjid Agung Demak diilhami bangunan langgar ini. Masjid Sunan Kalijaga ini lebih dahulu berdiri daripada Masjid Agung Demak. Baru pada zaman Pangeran Wijil, langgar Sunan Kalijaga itu dikembangkan menjadi sebuah masjid karena tuntutan jumlah jamaah. Sejak berdirinya hingga sekarang, masjid dengan bangunan induk yang asli berukuran 10 x 16 m ini telah mengalami beberapa kali perubahan dan perbaikan pada pemugaran karena tuntutan zaman dan jumlah jamaah yang semakin membludak. Perbaikan yang dilakukan secara besar-besaran dilakukan pada tahun 1970 dengan menambah beberapa bangunan serambi yang cukup luas.

Meski telah beberapa kali mengalami perbaikan, namun bangunan induk yang asli tidak pernah diubah, masih tetap dipertahankan keasliannya. Lebih-lebih keberadaan keempat tiang penyangga utama bangunan (sokoguru) yang oleh masyarakat setempat masih dikeramatkan dan masih berdiri kokoh menjadi saksi sejarah perkembangan Islam di Kadilangu dan sekitarnya. Keempat sokoguru itu terbuat dari kayu jati pilihan.

Pada tahun 1990, pengurus Masjid Sunan Kalijaga kembali melakukan pembangunan fisik meliputi tempat shalat dan tempat wudhu putri yang terpisah dengan pria.

Masjid ini berdiri di tengah-tengah masyarakat santri dan sudah tentu syiar masjid ini sangat membanggakan. Ini terlihat dari kegiatan pengajian yang marak di masjid ini. Juga pendidikan Madrasah Diniyah dan TPA tidak ketinggalan melengkapi kemakmuran masjid “langgar”nya Sunan Kalijaga ini
textTranslated:
There is almost something that is missed from observation, when we try to track and inventory historical mosques that played a big role in the spread and development of Islam in the country, namely the existence of the Sunan Kalijaga Mosque in Kadilangu, Demak Regency, Central Java.

Indeed, the existence of this sacred building seems to be drowned out by the great name of the Great Mosque of Demak, so it is rarely discussed in history. However, if we observe and look carefully at the existing inscriptions, the role of this mosque in the spread and development of Islam, especially in Java, is no less important than other historical mosques.

The Sunan Kalijaga Mosque is located in Kadilangu Village, Demak, just a few meters east of the Tomb Complex of Sunan Kalijaga and his family in Kadilangu—the graves of his wife and father (Raden Wilotikto).

The exact date and year of this ancient mosque's founding is not known, including the figure who founded it. However, from the existing inscriptions stored in the mosque, it is known that the Sunan Kalijaga Mosque was first renovated in 1564 AD by Prince Wijil.

It's just which Prince Wijil is meant, because in history it is known that there were five Prince Wijil from I to V. All of them were the successors of Sunan Kalijaga in the Kadilangu area and its surroundings. What is interesting from the sources of belief among the people of Kadilangu and its surroundings is that the Sunan Kalijaga Mosque was originally a langgar (surau/mushala) made by Sunan Kalijaga before he founded the Grand Mosque of Demak.

According to stories from previous parents, it is believed that the origin of the Great Mosque of Demak was inspired by this broken building. The Sunan Kalijaga Mosque was founded earlier than the Great Mosque of Demak. It was only during the time of Prince Wijil that the Sunan Kalijaga langgar was developed into a mosque due to the demands of the number of worshipers. Since its founding until now, the mosque with its original main building measuring 10 x 16 m has undergone several changes and restoration improvements due to the demands of the times and the increasing number of worshipers. Major repairs were carried out in 1970 by adding several large porches.

Even though it has undergone several repairs, the original main building has never been changed, its authenticity is still maintained. Moreover, the existence of the four main supporting pillars of the building (sokoguru) which the local community still holds sacred and still stands firmly is a witness to the history of the development of Islam in Kadilangu and its surroundings. The four pillars are made from selected teak wood.

In 1990, the management of the Sunan Kalijaga Mosque carried out physical construction again, including a prayer area and a place for women's ablutions which were separate from men's.

This mosque stands in the midst of the Islamic boarding school community and of course the publicity of this mosque is very proud. This can be seen from the recitation activities that are widespread in this mosque. address: Mendin, Paseban, Bayat, Klaten Regency, Central Java 57462, Indonesia
name: Nz Studio
text:
Sumber : channel Youtube  kampung Aswaja

makam sunan bayat yang berada di Desa Paseban, Kecamatan Bayat, Klaten, Jawa Tengah.
Sunan Pandanaran merupakan salah satu wali penyebar agama Islam di daerah tembayat pada zaman Kerajaan Demak. Beliau juga merupakan bupati pertama semarang dan salah satu murid Sunan Kalijaga.
Kompleks Makam Sunan Bayat dibangun di atas Gunung Jabalkat, sehingga untuk menuju ke atas perlu mendaki kurang lebih 200-an anak tangga. Disepanjang perjalanan kanan dan kiri dipenuhi dengan penjual pernak Pernik maupun oleh oleh khas bayat yang menarik.
Ketika sampai di tangga terakhir, terdapat masjid kecil yang bernama Masjid Sunan Bayat yang memiliki dua bedug di kanan kiri pintu masuknya. Masjid ini berarsitektur rumah Joglo atau rumah daerah khas Jawa. Nah disinilah rombongan melaksanakan solat mgrib  berjamaah setelah kembalinya berziarah dr makam. Nah bagi sobat kampung aswaja yang masih penasaran dan pengen tau apa saja karomah beliau silahkan  kunjungi channel kampung Aswaja
textTranslated:
Source: Aswaja village YouTube channel

Sunan Bayat's grave is in Paseban Village, Bayat District, Klaten, Central Java.
Sunan Pandanaran was one of the guardians who spread Islam in the tembayat area during the era of the Demak Kingdom. He was also the first regent of Semarang and one of Sunan Kalijaga's students.
The Sunan Bayat Tomb Complex was built on Mount Jabalkat, so to get to the top you need to climb approximately 200 steps. Along the way, the right and left are filled with sellers of knick-knacks and interesting typical bayat souvenirs.
When you reach the last stairs, there is a small mosque called the Sunan Bayat Mosque which has two drums on either side of the entrance. This mosque has the architecture of a Joglo house or a typical Javanese house. So, this is where the group performed the morning prayer together after returning from the pilgrimage to the grave. So, for Aswaja village friends who are still curious and want to know what his karomah is, please visit the Aswaja village channel.
title: Makam Sunan Bayat Ki Ageng Pandanaran

Hopefully you will be given good health so you can always visit his grave. Amen..

name: IDjo Royo Royo
text:
Ki Ageng Pandanaran seorang murid yang cerdas dan rajin. Berkat kecerdesannya, ia ditugaskan untuk menyiarkan agama Islam di sekitar daerah tersebut. Ia pun mendirikan sebuah perguruan di Gunung Jabalkat. Ajaran Ki Ageng Pandanaran yang paling menonjol dikenal dengan istilah Patembayatan, yaitu kerukunan dan kegotongroyongan. Setiap orang yang datang untuk memeluk agama Islam harus mengucapkan Sahadat Tembayat. Berkat ajaran Patembayatan, ia juga berhasil mendirikan sebuah masjid di Bukit Gala.

Selain pengetahuan agama, Ki Ageng Pandanaran juga mengajarkan cara bercocok tanam dan cara bergaul dengan baik kepada penduduk sekitarnya. Setelah itu, ia pun menetap di Jabalkat hingga akhir hayatnya. Daerah Jabalkat dan sekitarnya sekarang dikenal dengan nama Tembayat atau Bayat. Itulah sebabnya ia diberi gelar Sunan Tembayat atau Sunan Bayat. Hingga kini, makam Ki Ageng Pandanaran dapat ditemukan di atas Bukit Cakrakembang di sebelah selatan bukit Jabalkat, Desa Paseban, Kecamatan Bayat, Kabupaten Klaten.

*

Demikian cerita Ki Ageng Pandanaran dari daerah Klaten, Jawa Tengah, Indonesia. Cerita di atas termasuk kategori cerita sejarah yang mengandung pesan-pesan moral. Salah satunya adalah bahwa jangan sampai kemewahan duniawi membuat kita lupa diri seperti Ki Ageng Penandaran. Oleh karena sibuk mengejar kemewahan duniawi, akhirnya ia lupa pada kehidupan akhirat yang kekal. Namun, sejelek-jelek perbuatan seeorang, jika ia segera bertaubat, maka Tuhan akan mengampuni dan manusia pun akan memaafkannya. Berkat kesadarannya ingin cepat bertaubat, Ki Ageng Pandanaran direstui menjadi murid Sunan Kalijaga hingga akhirnya menjadi seorang sunan penyebar agama Islam di Jawa Tengah pada masa lalu dan terus dikenang hingga saat ini.
textTranslated:
Ki Ageng Pandanaran is a smart and diligent student. Thanks to his intelligence, he was assigned to broadcast Islam around the area. He also founded a college on Mount Jabalkat. Ki Ageng Pandanaran's most prominent teachings are known as Patembayatan, namely harmony and mutual cooperation. Everyone who comes to embrace Islam must say Sahadat Tembayat. Thanks to Patembayatan's teachings, he also succeeded in establishing a mosque on Gala Hill.

Apart from religious knowledge, Ki Ageng Pandanaran also taught how to grow crops and how to get along well with the surrounding residents. After that, he lived in Jabalkat until the end of his life. The Jabalkat area and its surroundings are now known as Tembayat or Bayat. That is why he was given the title Sunan Tembayat or Sunan Bayat. Until now, Ki Ageng Pandanaran's grave can be found on top of Cakrakembang Hill to the south of Jabalkat Hill, Paseban Village, Bayat District, Klaten Regency.

*

That is the story of Ki Ageng Pandanaran from the Klaten area, Central Java, Indonesia. The story above is included in the category of historical stories that contain moral messages. One of them is that we should not let worldly luxuries make us forget ourselves like Ki Ageng Penandaran. Because he was busy pursuing worldly luxuries, he finally forgot about the eternal life of the afterlife. However, no matter how bad a person's actions are, if he immediately repents, God will forgive him and humans will forgive him. Thanks to his awareness of wanting to quickly repent, Ki Ageng Pandanaran was given permission to become a student of Sunan Kalijaga and eventually became a Sunan who spread Islam in Central Java in the past and continues to be remembered to this day.
title: Makam Sunan Bayat Ki Ageng Pandanaran

address: Jl. Menara, Pejaten, Langgardalem, Kec. Kota Kudus, Kabupaten Kudus, Jawa Tengah, Indonesia
name: Shazam
text:
Pertama kali saya datang k masjid Kudus ini. Salah satu masjid tua di pulau Jawa warisan jaman dulu yg dibangun oleh  Ja'far Shodiq yg dikenal dgn nama sunan kudus. Kurang afdol kalau datang k Kudus tidak sholat di masjid besarnya. Masjidnya sedang untuk ukuran besarnya, tp termasuk besar kalau di daerah. Atap masjid memakai kayu jati, ukiran jaman dahulu dgn paduan tembok modern. Ukiran jatinya terlihat bersih dgn penerangan lampu neon yg di tutup dgn ukiran jati pula. Menara juga tinggi. Untuk tempat sholat wanita Tersedia di lt 2 dgn sarana yg lengkap. Tersedia mukena, sajadah dan akquran jika ingin membaca. Tempat wudhu terbagi dua antara tempat akhwat Dan Ikhwan. Depan masjid tersedia aula yg cukup besar dan luas untuk istirahat para tamu. Sejuk, indah, bagus dan wangi. Depan masjid Kudus terdapat lapangan alun2 Kudus. Jadi jika ada yg mau main, anak2. Bisa datang atau menunggu di depan masjid di alun-alun nya.

#Tempat bersejarah
# salah satu masjid besar di pulau jawa
# recommended,
textTranslated:
The first time I came to this Kudus Mosque. One of the old mosques on the island of Java, a legacy of ancient times, was built by Ja'far Shodiq, known as Sunan Kudus. It's not perfect if you come to Kudus and don't pray in the big mosque. The mosque is medium in size, but quite large in the area. The roof of the mosque uses teak wood, ancient carvings combined with modern walls. The teak carvings look clean with neon lights covered with teak carvings too. The tower is also high. For women's prayer, it is available on the 2nd floor with complete facilities. There are mukenas, prayer mats and a Koran available if you want to read. The place for ablution is divided into two places for sisters and brothers. In front of the mosque, there is a hall which is large and spacious enough for guests to rest. Cool, beautiful, nice and fragrant. In front of the Kudus mosque is the Kudus square. So if anyone wants to play, kids. You can come or wait in front of the mosque in the square.

#Historic sites
# one of the large mosques on the island of Java
#recommended,
title: Masjid Al-Aqsha Menara Kudus

address: Jl. Menara, Pejaten, Langgardalem, Kec. Kota Kudus, Kabupaten Kudus, Jawa Tengah, Indonesia
name: Ibzi Afra
text:
Minggu, 23 Juni 2024.
Nama resmi dari Masjid Menara Kudus adalah Masjid Al-Aqsa Manarat Qudus. Berdirinya Masjid Menara Kudus tidak lepas sari peran Sunan Kudus yang bernama asli Syeh Jafar Shodiq feat sebagai pendiri dan pemrakarsa.

Masjid ini pertama kali didirikan pada tahun 956 Hijriah atau 1549 Masehi. Sementara peletakan batu pertama adalah menggunakan batu dari Baitul Maqdis di Palestina. Maka dari itulah masjid ini kemudian dinamakan dengan nama Masjid Al Aqsha.

Sunan Kudus memiliki cara yang bijaksana dalan berdakwah. Sunan Kudus menggunakan pendekatan fabian, yaitu menyesuaikan diri, menyerap, bersikap pragmatis, dan menempuh cara dengan melakukan kompromi parsial dengan semangat toleransi terhadap nilai-nilai budaya warga setempat yang kebanyakan memeluk agama Hindu.

Salah satu sikap toleransi yang diajarkan Sunan Kudus yaitu pantang menyembelih sapi dan memakan dagingnya. Hal tersebut dilakukan untuk menghormati warga masyarakat yang memelik agama Hindu.

Bahkan sampai saat ini,masyarakat Kudus mengganti daging sapi dengan daging kerbau atau ayam.

Masjid Menara Kudus memang tampak unik. Keunikan tersebut terlihat dari bangunan menara yang ada di sebelah tenggara masjid. Menara yang tersusun dari batubata merah tersebut meyerupai Nale Kulkul atau bangunan penyimpan kentongan di Bali. Melalui karakteristik inilah, Masjid Menara Kudus mencerminkan sikap tenggang rasa atau toleransi yang sudah ada sejak dahulu.

Perpaduan budaya dalam Masjid Menara Kudus terjadi karena cara penyampaian Sunan Kudus dalam mengajarkan Islam tetap menghormati masyarakat Kudus yang sudah memeluk ajaran Hindu.

Masjid Menara Kudus juga sudah ditetapkan menjadi Cagar Budaya kategori Situs Tingkat Nasional.
textTranslated:
Sunday, June 23, 2024.
The official name of the Kudus Tower Mosque is Al-Aqsa Manarat Qudus Mosque. The establishment of the Kudus Tower Mosque cannot be separated from the role of Sunan Kudus, whose real name is Syeh Jafar Shodiq, as the founder and initiator.

This mosque was first founded in 956 Hijriah or 1549 AD. Meanwhile, the first stone was laid using stones from Baitul Maqdis in Palestine. That's why this mosque was later called the Al Aqsa Mosque.

Sunan Kudus has a wise way of preaching. Sunan Kudus uses a Fabian approach, namely adapting, absorbing, being pragmatic, and adopting a method of making partial compromises with a spirit of tolerance towards the cultural values ​​of local residents, most of whom adhere to Hinduism.

One of the attitudes of tolerance taught by Sunan Kudus is abstaining from slaughtering cows and eating their meat. This was done to respect members of the community who follow the Hindu religion.

Even today, Kudus people replace beef with buffalo or chicken.

The Kudus Tower Mosque does look unique. This uniqueness can be seen from the tower building to the southeast of the mosque. The tower, which is composed of red bricks, resembles the Nale Kulkul or building for storing drums in Bali. Through these characteristics, the Kudus Tower Mosque reflects an attitude of tolerance or tolerance that has existed for a long time.

The combination of cultures in the Kudus Tower Mosque occurs because Sunan Kudus's way of teaching Islam still respects the people of Kudus who have embraced Hinduism.

The Kudus Tower Mosque has also been designated as a Cultural Heritage in the National Site category.
title: Masjid Al-Aqsha Menara Kudus

text:
Waktu pertama kali berkunjung ke sini justru pada malam hari, dan masih di beri kesempatan sholat isya secara berjamaah. Suasana cukup ramai  mengingat masjid ini merupakan salah satu saksi penyebaran Islam di tanah Jawa.

Agak sulit menemukan area parkir kendaraan, kebetulan berkunjung kesini memakai kendaran roda dua. Jadi, agak leluasa parkir di deretan toko area depan masjid hehe.

Keunikan masjid ini dari arsitektur luarnya yang indetik dengan bangunan candi hal ini menunjukan bawa saat itu telah terjadi proses akulturasi dalam penyebaran Islam di tanah Jawa.

Anda juga dapat menemukan berbagai pedagang sovenir maupun oleh-oleh disepanjang jalan menuju area masjid.

Salah satu hal yang berkesan waktu berwudu secara tidak sengaja menemukan sahabat saya waktu di pesantren. Vibes di dalam masjid sangat terasa historisnya.

Sangat recommended apabila anda di Kudus untuk berkunjung kesini, karena masjid ini merupakan ikon wisata religius kabupaten Kudus.
textTranslated:
When I first visited here it was at night, and there was still the opportunity to pray in congregation for Isha prayers. The atmosphere is quite busy considering that this mosque is one of the witnesses to the spread of Islam in Java.

It is a bit difficult to find a vehicle parking area, coincidentally visiting here using a two-wheeled vehicle. So, it's quite easy to park in the row of shops in the front area of ​​the mosque hehe.

The uniqueness of this mosque is that its external architecture is identical to the temple building, this shows that at that time there had been an acculturation process in the spread of Islam in Java.

You can also find various souvenir and gift sellers along the road to the mosque area.

One of the memorable things during ablution was accidentally finding my best friend at the Islamic boarding school. The vibe in the mosque feels very historical.

It is highly recommended if you are in Kudus to visit here, because this mosque is a religious tourism icon in Kudus district.
title: Masjid Al-Aqsha Menara Kudus

address: Mendin, Paseban, Bayat, Klaten Regency, Central Java 57462, Indonesia
name: my journey 213
text:
Sunan Bayat (nama lain: Pangeran Mangkubumi, Susuhunan Tembayat, Sunan Pandanaran (II), Ki Ageng Pandanaran, atau Wahyu Widayat) adalah tokoh penyebar agama Islam di Jawa,meskipun secara tradisional tidak termasuk sebagai Wali Songo. Makamnya terletak di perbukitan (”Gunung Jabalkat”) di wilayah Kecamatan Bayat, Klaten, Jawa Tengah, Dari sana pula ia menyebarkan ajaran Islam kepada masyarakat wilayah Mataram,hidup pada masa Kesultanan Demak (abad ke-16).

Ia adalah putra dari Ki Ageng Pandan Arang, bupati pertama Semarang. Sepeninggal Ki Ageng Pandan Arang, putranya, Pangeran Mangkubumi, menggantikannya sebagai bupati Semarang kedua. Alkisah, ia menjalankan pemerintahan dengan baik dan selalu patuh dengan ajaran – ajaran Islam seperti halnya mendiang ayahnya. Namun lama-kelamaan terjadilah perubahan. Ia yang dulunya sangat baik itu menjadi semakin pudar. Tugas-tugas pemerintahan sering pula dilalaikan, begitu pula mengenai perawatan pondok-pondok pesantren dan tempat-tempat ibadah.

Sultan Demak Bintara, yang mengetahui hal ini, lalu mengutus Sunan Kalijaga dari Kadilangu, Demak, untuk menyadarkannya. Semula Ki Ageng Pandanaran adalah orang yang selalu mendewakan harta keduniawian. Berkat bimbingan dan ajaran-ajaran Sunan Kalijaga, Ki Ageng Pandanaran bisa disadarkan dari sifatnya yang buruk itu yang akhirnya Ki Ageng Pandanaran berguru kepada Sunan Kalijaga dan menyamar sebagai penjual rumput. Akhirnya, sang bupati menyadari kelalaiannya, dan memutuskan untuk mengundurkan diri dari jabatan duniawi dan menyerahkan kekuasaan Semarang kepada adiknya.

Sunan Kalijaga menyarankan Ki Ageng Pandanaran untuk berpindah ke selatan, tanpa membawa harta, didampingi isterinya, melalui daerah yang sekarang dinamakan Salatiga, Boyolali, dan Wedi. Namun, diam-diam tanpa sepengetahuannya, sang istri membawa tongkat bambu yang di dalamnya dipenuhi permata. Dalam perjalanan mereka dihadang oleh kawanan perampok yang dipimpin oleh yang namanya sekarang disebut Syekh Domba.

Maka terjadilah perkelahian dan untung saja pasangan suami istri ini berhasil mengatasinya akhirnya Allah SWT murka kemudian dia berubah menjadi sebuah mahluk dengan perawakan manusia tetapi berkepala domba. Setelah terjadi demikian, akhirnya dia menyadari dan menyesal dengan segala perbuatannya, kemudian menyatakan diri sebagai pengikut Sunan Pandanaran yang kemudian dibawa oleh Sunan Pandanaran ke gurunya yaitu Sunan Kalijaga yang akhirnya kepala dia berubah kembali menjadi kepala manusia seperti semula. Setelah itu Syekh Domba diberi tugas untuk mengisi tempat wudhu pada padasan atau gentong pada masjid yang berada pada puncak bukit Jabalkat, Bayat.

Akhirnya Ki Ageng Pandanaran berhasil sampai dan menetap di Tembayat, yang sekarang bernama Bayat, dan menyiarkan Islam dari sana kepada para pertapa dan pendeta di sekitarnya. Karena kesaktiannya ia mampu meyakinkan mereka untuk memeluk agama Islam. Oleh karena itu ia disebut sebagai Sunan Tembayat atau Sunan Bayat.
textTranslated:
Sunan Bayat (other names: Pangeran Mangkubumi, Susuhunan Tembayat, Sunan Pandanaran (II), Ki Ageng Pandanaran, or Wahyu Widayat) is a figure who spread Islam in Java, although traditionally not included as a Wali Songo. His grave is located in the hills ("Mount Jabalkat") in the Bayat District, Klaten, Central Java. From there he also spread Islamic teachings to the people of the Mataram region, living during the Demak Sultanate (16th century).

He is the son of Ki Ageng Pandan Arang, the first regent of Semarang. After the death of Ki Ageng Pandan Arang, his son, Pangeran Mangkubumi, succeeded him as the second regent of Semarang. Once upon a time, he ran the government well and always obeyed the teachings of Islam like his late father. But over time changes occurred. He who was once very good became increasingly faded. Government duties are often neglected, as is the maintenance of Islamic boarding schools and places of worship.

The Sultan of Demak Bintara, who knew about this, then sent Sunan Kalijaga from Kadilangu, Demak, to wake him up. Initially, Ki Ageng Pandanaran was a person who always deified worldly possessions. Thanks to Sunan Kalijaga's guidance and teachings, Ki Ageng Pandanaran was awakened from his bad nature, so Ki Ageng Pandanaran finally learned from Sunan Kalijaga and disguised himself as a grass seller. Finally, the regent realized his negligence, and decided to resign from worldly office and hand over control of Semarang to his younger brother.

Sunan Kalijaga advised Ki Ageng Pandanaran to move south, without bringing any wealth, accompanied by his wife, through the areas now called Salatiga, Boyolali and Wedi. However, secretly without his knowledge, his wife brought a bamboo stick filled with jewels. On their way they were confronted by a group of robbers led by what is now called Sheikh Lamb.

So a fight broke out and fortunately the husband and wife managed to overcome it. Finally Allah SWT got angry and he turned into a creature with a human appearance but the head of a sheep. After this happened, he finally realized and regretted all his actions, then declared himself to be a follower of Sunan Pandanaran who was then taken by Sunan Pandanaran to his teacher, namely Sunan Kalijaga, whose head finally changed back to being a human head as before. After that, Sheikh Domba was given the task of filling the ablution place in the padasan or barrel at the mosque at the top of the Jabalkat hill, Bayat.

Finally Ki Ageng Pandanaran managed to arrive and settle in Tembayat, which is now called Bayat, and broadcast Islam from there to the hermits and priests in the surrounding area. Because of his supernatural powers he was able to convince them to embrace Islam. Therefore he is called Sunan Tembayat or Sunan Bayat.
title: Makam Sunan Bayat Ki Ageng Pandanaran

merupakan salah satu wisata religi atau ziarah makam yang berada di wilayah kabupaten Klaten. Keberadaannya cukup terkenal oleh para peziarah karena dalam sejarahnya merupakan wali penyebar agama Islam di tanah Jawa pada zaman Kerajaan Demak dan murid Sunan Kalijaga. Kompleks Makam Sunan Pandanaran menempati sebuah bukit dengan makam umum di bagian dasar hingga anak tangga kemudian kompleks makam utama berada di puncak bukit.

Makam Sunan Pandanaran atau biasa dikenal dengan sebutan Sunan Bayat (Tembayat) ini terletak di kelurahan Paseban, Kecamatan Bayat, Kabupaten Klaten. Makam ini konon dibangun sejak 1526 Masehi
textTranslated:
is one of the religious tours or grave pilgrimages in the Klaten district. Its existence is quite well known to pilgrims because historically it was the guardian of the spread of Islam in Java during the time of the Demak Kingdom and a student of Sunan Kalijaga. The Sunan Pandanaran Tomb Complex occupies a hill with a public tomb at the base to the steps, then the main tomb complex is at the top of the hill.

The tomb of Sunan Pandanaran or commonly known as Sunan Bayat (Tembayat) is located in Paseban sub-district, Bayat District, Klaten Regency. This tomb is said to have been built in 1526 AD

text:
