address: Mendin, Paseban, Bayat, Klaten Regency, Central Java 57462, Indonesia
name: Rangga dy
text:
Tempat wisata di Klaten yang terakhir dari kami adalah Makan sunan Pandanaran Bayat atau dikenal juga dengan beberapa nama yakni Sunan Bayat, Pangeran Mangkubumi, Susuhunan Tembayat, Sunan Pandanaran (II), atau Wahyu Widayat, adalah tokoh yang disebut sebut dalam sejarah lisan sebagai salah satu penyebar agama Islam di tanah Jawa meski tidak masuk dalam jajaran Wali Songo.

Ziarah ke Makam Sunan Pandanaran Klaten
Makamnya terletak di puncak gunung Jabalkat yang sebenarnya hanyalah sebuah bukit, di dalam wilayah Desa Paseban Bayat, Kecamatan Bayat, Kabupaten Klaten, Provinsi Jawa Tengah. Dan layaknya makam seorang wali makam Sunan Pandanaran Bayat tak penah sepi dari para peziarah yang datang dari berbagai pelosok Nusantara.
textTranslated:
The last tourist attraction in Klaten from us is Makan Sunan Pandanaran Bayat or also known by several names, namely Sunan Bayat, Pangeran Mangkubumi, Susuhunan Tembayat, Sunan Pandanaran (II), or Wahyu Widayat, is a figure mentioned in oral history as one of the spreader of Islam in Java even though he was not included in the ranks of the Wali Songo.

Pilgrimage to the Tomb of Sunan Pandanaran Klaten
His grave is located at the top of Mount Jabalkat, which is actually just a hill, in the Paseban Bayat Village area, Bayat District, Klaten Regency, Central Java Province. And like the grave of a saint, the tomb of Sunan Pandanaran Bayat is never empty of pilgrims who come from various corners of the archipelago.
title: Makam Sunan Bayat Ki Ageng Pandanaran

address: Mendin, Paseban, Bayat, Klaten Regency, Central Java 57462, Indonesia
name: Arif Syamsudin
text: Alhamdulillah, Situs yang patut disyukuri dan dapat dibanggakan bagi masyarakat kab. Klaten, karena tanpa diundang para peziarah dari penjuru manapun digerakkan Allah untuk datang ke klaten untuk mengadakan majlis do'a, mereka datang secara rombongan dari daerah seluruh Indonesia, sehingga secara tidak langsung menggerakkan roda perekonomian disekitar makam, karena masyarakat sekitar bisa melakukan usaha apapun sehingga ekonominya menjadi aktif ...
textTranslated: Alhamdulillah, a site that the people of the district should be grateful for and be proud of. Klaten, because without being invited, pilgrims from all over were moved by Allah to come to Klaten to hold a prayer service, they came in groups from regions all over Indonesia, thus indirectly moving the wheels of the economy around the tomb, because the local people could do any business so that the economy is becoming active...
title: Makam Sunan Bayat Ki Ageng Pandanaran

address: Mendin, Paseban, Bayat, Klaten Regency, Central Java 57462, Indonesia
name: Ir Sutrisno Darmomihardjo
text: Pendopo Pandanaran merupakan bangsal bagi para wisatawan religius yg berkunjung ziarah ke makam Sunan Pandanaran Bayat. Almarhum merupakan salah satu tokoh terkenal syiar agama Islam murid Sunan Kalijogo, dulu pernah diangkat sbg sebagai bupati Semarang dan dianggap sebagai pendiri kota Semarang. Setiap ulang tahun kota Semarang salah satu acaranya adalah ziarah ke makam ini.
textTranslated: Pendopo Pandanaran is a ward for religious tourists who visit the pilgrimage to the tomb of Sunan Pandanaran Bayat. The deceased was one of the well-known figures who spread Islam, a student of Sunan Kalijogo, who had previously been appointed as regent of Semarang and was considered the founder of the city of Semarang. address: Mendin, Paseban, Bayat, Klaten Regency, Central Java 57462, Indonesia
name: Bang Roey
text: Makam salah satu murid Sunan Kalijaga yang juga merupakan putra Raden Pandanaran I. Sunan Bayat memiliki nama asli Sunan Pandanaran II. Masih banyak yang bingung mengenai letak makam Sunan Bayat antara di Bergas, Semarang atau di Klaten. Sebenarnya perbedaannya jelas. Makam Sunan Bayat terletak di Gunung Jabalkat, Bayat, Klaten sesuai dengan arahan Sunan Kalijaga ketika hendak diterima menjadi murid beliau. Sedangkan makam di Bergas merupakan makam ayahanda dari Sunan Bayat. Ayahanda Sunan Bayat atau Sunan Pandanaran I dikenal sebagai pendiri kota Semarang.
textTranslated: The grave of one of Sunan Kalijaga's students who was also the son of Raden Pandanaran I. Sunan Bayat's real name was Sunan Pandanaran II. Many people are still confused about the location of Sunan Bayat's grave, whether in Bergas, Semarang or Klaten. Actually the difference is clear. Sunan Bayat's grave is located on Mount Jabalkat, Bayat, Klaten in accordance with Sunan Kalijaga's instructions when he wanted to be accepted as his student. Meanwhile, the grave in Bergas is the grave of Sunan Bayat's father. Sunan Bayat's father or Sunan Pandanaran I is known as the founder of the city of Semarang.
title: Makam Sunan Bayat Ki Ageng Pandanaran

Baru pertamakali berkunjung kesini, sangat takjub saya melihat bangunan dan ornamen di tempat ini,
Waktu itu kami rombongan dalam rangka program kerja juga,
Sayangnya tiba di tempat ini sudah malam jelang dini hari, jadi saya pribadi tidak sempat menggali informasi yang lebih detail tentang masjid ini, karena tujuan utamanya memang untuk ziaroh saja,
Habis itu ada tujuan ketempat yang lain ke kota solo, menyambangi Masjid Sheikh Sayyed
textTranslated:
This is my first time visiting here, I was really amazed to see the buildings and ornaments in this place,
At that time we were a group for a work program too,
Unfortunately, when I arrived at this place it was already late in the morning, so I personally didn't have time to dig up more detailed information about this mosque, because its main purpose was just for pilgrimage.
After that, we went to another place, to the city of Solo, visiting the Sheikh Sayyed Mosque
title: Masjid Al-Aqsha Menara Kudus

address: Jl. Menara, Pejaten, Langgardalem, Kec. Kota Kudus, Kabupaten Kudus, Jawa Tengah, Indonesia
name: Istianah
text: Tempat wudhu wanita membingungkan, harus pakai sandal untuk menuju tempat wudhu, laki2 masih bisa lewat situ dan petunjuk arah tidak jelas, mukena di masjid sangat bau. Tidak ada managemenkah masjidnya?? Sangat disayangkan, orang mau ibadah agak terganggu. Padahal infaq dan shodaqoh banyak sekali.
textTranslated: The ablution area for women is confusing, you have to wear sandals to get to the ablution area, men can still pass there and the directions are not clear, the mukena in the mosque is very smelly. Is there no management at the mosque?? It's a shame that people who want to worship are somewhat disturbed. Even though there is a lot of infaq and shodaqoh.
title: Masjid Al-Aqsha Menara Kudus

text:
Tempat untuk ziarah salah satu saints (wali) penyebar agama Islam di Jawa. Arsitektur unik, jawa klasik, sinkretisme antara gaya hindu dan islam.

Lokasi bersih, tertata baik, dan free htm
Banyak pedagang oleh-oleh, try jenang or permen tape/sirsak, they’re most recommended.
textTranslated:
A place for pilgrimage to one of the saints (guardians) who spread Islam in Java. Unique architecture, classic Javanese, syncretism between Hindu and Islamic styles.

The location is clean, well organized, and free htm
There are lots of souvenir sellers, try jenang or tape/soursop candy, they're most recommended.

text:
Menara Kudus adalah sebuah tempat yang menakjubkan!
Saya sangat terkesan dengan keindahan arsitektur yang megah dan sejarah yang kaya di balik bangunan ini. Pengalaman saya mengunjungi Menara Kudus benar-benar luar biasa. Dari atas menara, pemandangan kota Kudus begitu menakjubkan, terutama saat matahari terbenam.
Saya juga terkesan dengan keramahan staf di sini, mereka sangat membantu dan ramah. Tempat ini sangat layak untuk dikunjungi bagi siapa pun yang ingin merasakan keindahan dan sejarah kota Kudus.
Saya pasti akan merekomendasikan Menara Kudus kepada teman dan keluarga saya. Terima kasih atas pengalaman yang luar biasa!
textTranslated:
The Holy Tower is an amazing place!
I was very impressed by the majestic beauty of the architecture and the rich history behind this building. My experience visiting the Kudus Tower was truly extraordinary. From the top of the tower, the view of Kudus city is amazing, especially at sunset.
I was also impressed by the friendliness of the staff here, they were very helpful and friendly. This place is very worth visiting for anyone who wants to experience the beauty and history of the city of Kudus.
I will definitely recommend Menara Kudus to my friends and family. Thank you for a great experience!
title: Masjid Al-Aqsha Menara Kudus

textTranslated: is an ancient mosque built by Sunan Kudus since 1549 AD (956 Hijriah). The current location is in Kauman Village, Kota District, Kudus Regency, Central Java. This mosque is unique because it has a tower that is similar to a temple building and an architectural pattern that combines Islamic cultural concepts with Hindu-Buddhist culture, thereby showing the process of acculturation in Javanese Islam.

name: Setionoegroho Spm
text:
Masjid Menara Kudus, adalah masjid kuno peninggalan sejarah peradaban Islam di kota Kudus, dibangun oleh Sunan Kudus (Walisongo) pada tahun 1546 M.
Keunikan dari masjid ini pada menaranya yang menyerupai bangunan candi dengan perpaduan arsitektur berkonsep budaya Islam dengan budaya Hindu-Budha. Hal ini menunjukkan bahwa pada saat itu  terjadi proses akulturasi dalam pengembangan Islam di Jawa. Termasuk dalam berdakwah pun, Sunan Kudus melakukan pendekatan kultural (budaya), karena  di tengah masyarakat telah memiliki budaya mapan yang telah dipengaruh agama Hindu dan Buddha.
Di sisi barat masjid, terdapat makam Sunan Kudus, yang banyak diziarahi oleh masyarakat dari sekitar maupun dari luar kota Kudus.
textTranslated:
The Kudus Tower Mosque, is an ancient mosque, a historical heritage of Islamic civilization in the city of Kudus, built by Sunan Kudus (Walisongo) in 1546 AD.
The uniqueness of this mosque is that its tower resembles a temple building with an architectural combination of Islamic cultural concepts and Hindu-Buddhist culture. This shows that at that time there was a process of acculturation in the development of Islam in Java. Even in preaching, Sunan Kudus takes a cultural approach, because society already has an established culture that has been influenced by Hinduism and Buddhism.
On the west side of the mosque, there is the tomb of Sunan Kudus, which is visited by many people from around and outside the city of Kudus.
title: Masjid Al-Aqsha Menara Kudus

text:
Hanya beberapa kali datang ke tempat ini, tetapi sudah memberikan kesan yang bikin rindu untuk datang kembali, bangunan yang estetik berupa menara yang sangat Legend, masjid yang indah sangat nyaman untuk ibadah,  ditambah ada maqbaroh Sunan Kudus, paket lengkap.
Kalau rombongan naik bis, harus naik ojek terlebih dahulu untuk sampai ke lokasi. Tempatnya disini sangat umum, tidak seperti tempat yang lain, yang rata-rata hanya untuk orang yang mau ziaroh, tapi ditempat ini banyak pengunjung yang hanya untuk menikmati tempat disini, berkumpul juga pemukiman penduduk.
Tempat belanja yang banyak juga bukan di sekitar masjid, tetapi di terminal tempat Bis diparkir. Di sekitar masjid yang banyak orang jualan makanan ringan.
Alhamdulillah semoga ditempatkan untuk berkunjung ke tempat ini, dan semoga mendapat barokah dari Sunan Kudus. Aamiiiin yaa Robbal 'Alamin...
textTranslated:
I've only been to this place a few times, but it already gives an impression that makes me long to come back, the aesthetic building is a very legendary tower, the beautiful mosque is very comfortable for worship, plus there is the Sunan Kudus maqbaroh, a complete package.
If the group takes the bus, they must take a motorbike taxi first to get to the location. The place here is very public, unlike other places, which are generally only for people who want to make a pilgrimage, but in this place there are many visitors who just enjoy the place here, there are also residential areas gathered.
There are also many shopping places not around the mosque, but at the terminal where the buses are parked. Around the mosque there are many people selling snacks.
Alhamdulillah, I hope you are given the opportunity to visit this place, and hopefully you will receive blessings from Sunan Kudus. Aamiin ya Robbal 'Alamin...
title: Masjid Al-Aqsha Menara Kudus

Religious tourism, education, evidence of the legacy of Islamic civilization in Indonesia.
Funeral complex, mosque and tower of the Sunan Kudus tomb.
It is recommended to maintain attitudes & norms when entering the building.
It is one of the mandatory tourist destinations when visiting Kudus.
Limited parking space.

The location is easy to find, because it is not far from the city center / Kudus square.
Surrounded by various souvenir shops & souvenirs typical of Kudus.

- Tickets

text: masjid kuno yang dibangun oleh Sunan Kudus sejak tahun 1549 Masehi (956 Hijriyah). Lokasi saat ini berada di Desa Kauman, Kecamatan Kota, Kabupaten Kudus, Jawa Tengab. Ada keunikan dari masjid ini karena memiliki menara yang serupa bangunan candi serta pola arsitektur yang memadukan konsep budaya Islam dengan budaya Hindu-Budis sehingga menunjukkan terjadinya proses akukturasi dalam pengislaman Jawa
textTranslated: An ancient mosque built by Sunan Kudus dating back to 1549 AD (956 Hijriyah). The current location is in Kauman Village, Kota District, Kudus Regency, Central Java. This mosque is unique because it has a tower that is similar to a temple building and an architectural pattern that combines Islamic cultural concepts with Hindu-Buddhist culture, thereby showing the process of acceleration in Javanese Islam.
title: Masjid Al-Aqsha Menara Kudus

address: Jl. Menara, Pejaten, Langgardalem, Kec. Kota Kudus, Kabupaten Kudus, Jawa Tengah, Indonesia
name: Faisal Reza Sukmawan
text:
Masjid yang tidak terlalu besar namun kaya akan nilai sejarah budaya, masjid dengan menara ikonik yang bergaya Hindu ini dibangun oleh Sunan Kudus (Raden Ja'far Shadiq) sebagai simbol akulturasi budaya dan bukti bahwa agama Islam disebarkan dengan cara yang elegan di tanah jawa khususnya di wilayah Kudus dan sekitarnya.

Masjid dan menara ini juga merupakan salah satu obyek wisata religi yang berada di kabupaten Kudus, makam Sunan Kudus sendiri berada di dalam area masjid dan selalu ramai akan jamaah/peziarah yang datang dari berbagai macam daerah, beberapa paket tour religi/ziarah bahkan menjadikan masjid ini sebagai tujuan yang wajib dikunjungi karena masjid ini memang termasuk dalam daftar masjid peninggalan para wali apalagi yang paling masyhur adalah walisongo dan Sunan Kudus adalah salah satu diantaranya.

Untuk area masjid sendiri tidak terlalu luas, berada di area padat/perkotaan dengan jalan yang tidak terlalu lebar dan kendaraan bermotor yang lalu lalang sehingga jika banyak pengunjung membuat jalanan macet, area parkir kendaraan roda empat juga cukup kecil.
textTranslated:
A mosque that is not too big but is rich in historical and cultural value, this mosque with an iconic Hindu-style minaret was built by Sunan Kudus (Raden Ja'far Sadiq) as a symbol of cultural acculturation and proof that the Islamic religion was spread in an elegant way in Java, especially in Kudus area and surrounding areas.

This mosque and tower is also one of the religious tourist attractions in Kudus district, the tomb of Sunan Kudus itself is in the mosque area and is always busy with worshipers/pilgrims coming from various regions, several religious/pilgrimage tour packages even make this mosque as a destination that must be visited because this mosque is included in the list of mosques left by the saints, especially as the most famous is the walisongo and Sunan Kudus is one of them.

The mosque area itself is not very large, it is in a dense/urban area with roads that are not too wide and motorized vehicles passing by so that if there are lots of visitors the road becomes congested, the parking area for four-wheeled vehicles is also quite small.
title: Masjid Al-Aqsha Menara Kudus

address: Jl. Menara, Pejaten, Langgardalem, Kec. Kota Kudus, Kabupaten Kudus, Jawa Tengah, Indonesia
name: Muhtamah Nur Habibah (mukhtsz)
text:
Masjid kuno yang dibangun oleh Sunan Kudus, dengan keunikannya yang memiliki menara yang serupa bangunan candi dengan pola konsep bangunan pemaduan budaya islam dan Hindu-Buddha, yang menjadi bukti akulturasi budaya Hindu-Buddha dalam dakwah Islam yang dilakukan oleh Sunan Kudus.
Penamaan Masjid Al-Aqsha ini dikarenakan batu yang digunakan untuk peletakan batu pertama menggunakan batu dari Baitul Maqdis di Palestina.

untuk berkunjung ke sini tidak dikenakan biaya retribusi alias gratis.
untuk parkir motor sendiri bisa parkir di sebrang masjid sebesar dengan membayar 5000.
textTranslated:
The ancient mosque built by Sunan Kudus, with its uniqueness, has a tower similar to a temple building with a building concept pattern that combines Islamic and Hindu-Buddhist culture, which is proof of the acculturation of Hindu-Buddhist culture in Islamic preaching carried out by Sunan Kudus.
The name Al-Aqsa Mosque is because the stone used for laying the first stone was stone from Baitul Maqdis in Palestine.

There is no fee to visit here, aka it's free.
To park your own motorbike, you can park opposite the mosque by paying 5000.
title: Masjid Al-Aqsha Menara Kudus

text: Masjid ini mulai didirikan pada tahun 956 H atau 1549 M. Peletakan batu pertama menggunakan batu dari Baitul Maqdis di Palestina, oleh karena itu masjid ini kemudian dinamakan Masjid Al Aqsha.
textTranslated: This mosque was founded in 956 H or 1549 AD. This is based on an Arabic inscription written on a stone inscription measuring 30 cm wide and 46 cm long located on the mosque's mihrab. The first stone was laid using stones from Baitul Maqdis in Palestine, therefore this mosque was later named Al Aqsa Mosque.

text:
MASJID DAN ASAL-USUL NAMA KOTA KUDUS SERTA MITOS

Kunjungan 17 Maret 2022.

Seperti yang telah disampaikan di postingan sebelumnya bahwasanya masjid buatan Sunan Kudus mengadopsi arsitektur bercorak Hindu Budha hal ini terlihat dari pintu gerbang dan menara masjid nama untuk arsitektur lainnya berbaur dengan corak Arab dan Islam.

Semula diberi nama Al Manar atau Masjid Al Aqsho, meniru nama Masjid di Yerussalem yang bernama Masjidil Aqsho. Kota Yerussalem juga disebut Baitul Maqdis atau Al-Quds. Dari kata Al-Quds tersebut kemudian lahir kata Kudus, yang kemudian digunakan untuk nama kota Kudus sekarang.

Sebelumnya mungkin bernama Loaram, dan nama ini masih dipakai sebagai nama Desa Loram sampai sekarang. Masjid buatan Sunan Kudus tersebut dikenal dengan nama masjid Menara di Kauman Kulon. Sejak Sunan Kudus bertempat tinggal di daerah itu, jumlah kaum muslimin makin bertambah sehingga daerah disekitar Masjid diberi nama Kauman, yang berarti tempat tinggal kaum muslimin.

Terdapat mitos juga yang menyatakan bahwasanya di pintu gerbang masjid oleh Sunan Kudus ditanam raja kalacakra tujuannya untuk melindungi area masjid dari orang-orang yang tidak berniat baik.

Terlepas benar atau tidaknya namun ada juga yang mengatakan jika pejabat ada yang datang ke Kudus maka ia akan lengser dari kekuasaannya ini terjadi pada presiden Bung Karno dan gusdur. Beberapa pejabat lain jika ada yang menghindari daerah Kudus termasuk pembatalan kunjungan presiden Jokowi.

Di samping pintu menara masjid sebelah kiri ada pintu itu dengan motif gapura untuk akses menuju makam Sunan Kudus yang akan saya infokan di postingan berikutnya insya Allah.

textTranslated:
MOSQUE AND THE ORIGIN OF THE NAME OF THE HOLY CITY AND MYTHS

Visit March 17, 2022.

As stated in the previous post, the mosque made by Sunan Kudus adopted Hindu-Buddhist architecture, this can be seen from the gate and tower of the mosque, the name of the other architecture blending with Arabic and Islamic patterns.

Originally given the name Al Manar or Al Aqsho Mosque, imitating the name of the mosque in Jerusalem called Al Aqsho Mosque. The city of Jerusalem is also called Baitul Maqdis or Al-Quds. From the word Al-Quds, the word Kudus was born, which was then used as the name of the current city of Kudus.

Previously it was probably called Loaram, and this name is still used as the name of Loram Village today. The mosque made by Sunan Kudus is known as the Menara Mosque in Kauman Kulon. Since Sunan Kudus lived in that area, the number of Muslims increased so that the area around the mosque was given the name Kauman, which means the place where the Muslims live.

There is also a myth which states that Sunan Kudus planted a kalachakra king at the gate of the mosque to protect the mosque area from people who did not have good intentions.

Regardless of whether it is true or not, there are also those who say that if an official comes to Kudus then he will step down from power. This happened to President Bung Karno and Gusdur. Several other officials, if any, are avoiding the Kudus area, including canceling President Jokowi's visit.

Next to the door of the mosque tower on the left there is a door with a gate motif for access to the tomb of Sunan Kudus which I will inform you about in the next post, God willing.

text:
Masjid Menara Kudus merupakan salah satu masjid kuno yang dibangun oleh Sunan Kudus sejak tahun 1579 Masehi.

Terletak di Desa Kauman, Kecamatan Kota, Kabupaten Kudus, Jawa Tengah.

Hal yang menjadi keunikan dari masjid ini adalah memiliki menara yang serupa bangunan candi serta pola arsitektur yang memadukan konsep budaya Islam dengan budaya Hindu-Buddhis sehingga menunjukkan terjadinya proses akulturasi dalam pengislaman Jawa.

Sehari-hari, peziarah berkunjung ke masjid ini untuk beribadah sekaligus ziarah ke makam Sunan Kudus yang terletak di sisi barat kompleks masjid. Selain itu, masjid ini menjadi pusat keramaian pada Festival Dhandhangan yang diadakan warga Kudus untuk menyambut bulan suci Ramadan.

Sumber: Wikipedia
textTranslated:
The Kudus Tower Mosque is one of the ancient mosques built by Sunan Kudus since 1579 AD.

Located in Kauman Village, Kota District, Kudus Regency, Central Java.

What is unique about this mosque is that it has a tower that is similar to a temple building and an architectural pattern that combines Islamic cultural concepts with Hindu-Buddhist culture, thereby showing the process of acculturation in Javanese Islam.

Every day, pilgrims visit this mosque to worship as well as make a pilgrimage to the tomb of Sunan Kudus which is located on the west side of the mosque complex. Apart from that, this mosque is the center of the crowd at the Dhandhangan Festival held by Kudus residents to welcome the holy month of Ramadan.

Source: Wikipedia

text: Masjid Al-Aqsha Menara Kudus. Salah satu masjid legendaris yang memiliki arsitektur yg cukup unik. Menara Kudus yang ada di depan masjid masih aktif digunakan untuk tempat menabuh bedug menjelang kumandang adzan shalat wajib 5 waktu. Selain itu, terdapat makam Sunan Kudus (salah satu tokoh Walisongo). Terdapat pula parkiran untuk motor di samping masjid, namun parkiran untuk mobil agak susah. Suasana masjid ramai dikunjungi peziarah, dan juga terdapat SMP di dekat masjid, sehingga banyak anak² di pagi hari menjelang masuk kelas. Di sepanjang jalan menuju masjid juga banyak sekali toko oleh² khas Kudus yang bertema Islam, seperti baju takwa, wewangian, jenang, dll.
textTranslated: Al-Aqsa Mosque, Kudus Tower. One of the legendary mosques that has quite unique architecture. The Kudus Tower in front of the mosque is still actively used as a place to beat the drum before the call to prayer for the five obligatory prayers. Apart from that, there is the tomb of Sunan Kudus (one of the Walisongo figures). There is also parking for motorbikes next to the mosque, but parking for cars is a bit difficult. The mosque is busy with pilgrims, and there is also a junior high school near the mosque, so there are lots of children in the morning before class. Along the road to the mosque there are also lots of typical Kudus souvenir shops with Islamic themes, such as pious clothes, perfumes, jenang, etc.

name: Toriqoh Aufa
text:
Siang itu saya dan dua orang teman saya berangkat dari Jepara menuju Menara Kudus dengan naik angkutan umum bis kecil, kami naik bis dari pom bensin sengon Bugel lalu bis berhenti di terminal Jetak. Setelah itu kami melanjutkan perjalanan dengan naik angkot.

Rencana nya kami mau berziarah lalu mampir lihat Dhandhangan. Ya "Dhandhangan" satu kata yang sedikit asing terdengar olehku yang bukan asli orang sana.

Biasanya temen- temen kerjaku suka nanya gini "Dek, wis tilik ndandangan tah durung? Ayok rono bareng- bareng, ngko nek kono numpak dermolen" ( Dek, sudah liat dandangan belum? Ayok kesana bareng bareng, nanti disana naik dermolen)

Aku nggak langsung jawab, mikir sebentar. Terus njawab gini "mbak, dermolen iku opo?" (Mbak, dermolen itu apa?)

"Iku loh dek, sing koyo kurungan manuk, muter-muter" (Itu loh dek, yang seperti kurungan manuk berputar-putar)

"Oh, bianglala tah mbak" (Oh, bianglala ternyata mbak)

Memasuki 2 atau 1 minggu sebelum puasa pasti ada tradisi dandangan di Kudus, dandangan akan selesai dihari pertama puasa.

(Dandangan itu apa yaaa?? Dandangan/Dhandhangan/Ndandangan itu sebuah tradisi yang ada di Kudus. Semacam festival, tetapi pedagang menjajakan dagangannya ditengah jalan raya di sepanjang  jalan sekitar menara Kudus sampai alun alun. Beraneka macam kuliner, pernak pernik, pakaian, dll tertata sangat menarik).

Dan pengetahuanku tentang bahasa di sini bertambah lagi. Ini versi ku, mohon maaf jika masih banyak kesalahan tentang tulisan ini.

Pas sekali Minggu itu adalah hari terakhir Dhandhangan sebelum bulan puasa tahun 2019. Ramai sekali pengunjung.
textTranslated:
That afternoon, two of my friends and I departed from Jepara to Kudus Tower by public transportation, a small bus, we took the bus from the Sengon Bugel gas station and then the bus stopped at the Jetak terminal. After that we continued our journey by public transportation.

Our plan was to make a pilgrimage and then stop by to see Dhandhangan. Yes, "Dhandhangan" is a word that sounds a little foreign to me who is not native there.

Usually my work friends like to ask something like this, "Sir, are you looking at the ndandangan tah durung? Let's go rono together, ngko nek kono numpak dermolen" (Dek, have you seen the dandangan yet? Let's go there together, then there we'll ride the dermolen)

I didn't answer right away, thought for a moment. Then he answered like this, "Sis, what's wrong with dermolen?" (Sis, what is dermolen?)

"Here you go, sing koyo manuk cage, go round and round" (That's what you see, which is like a manuk cage going round and round)

"Oh, it's a Ferris wheel, sis" (Oh, it's a Ferris wheel, sis)

Entering 2 or 1 weeks before fasting, there is definitely a tradition of grooming in Kudus, the grooming will be finished on the first day of fasting.

(What is Dandangan?? Dandangan/Dhandhangan/Ndandangan is a tradition in Kudus. It's a kind of festival, but traders sell their wares in the middle of the main road along the road around the Kudus tower to the main square. Various kinds of culinary delights, knick-knacks, clothes, etc. very interesting arrangement).

And my knowledge of the language here has increased even more. This is my version, sorry if there are still many mistakes in this article.

Fittingly, Sunday was the last day of Dhandhangan before the fasting month of 2019. There were lots of visitors.

address: Jl. Menara, Pejaten, Langgardalem, Kec. Kota Kudus, Kabupaten Kudus, Jawa Tengah, Indonesia
name: Muhammad Farokhi
text:
Berdirinya Masjid Menara Kudus tidak terlepas dari peran Sunan Kudus sebagai penggagas dan pendiri. Sebagaimana Walisongo yang lainnya, Sunan Kudus menggunakan pendekatan kultural (budaya) dalam berdakwah. Ia mengadaptasi dan melakukan pribumisasi ajaran Islam di tengah masyarakat yang telah memiliki budaya mapan dalam pengaruh agama Hindu dan Buddha. Akulturasi budaya Hindu dan Budha dalam dakwah Islam yang dilakukan Sunan Kudus terlihat jelas pada arsitektur dan konsep bangunan Masjid Menara Kudus.

Masjid ini mulai didirikan pada tahun 956 H atau 1549 M. Hal ini didasarkan pada inskripsi berbahasa Arab yang tertulis pada prasasti batu berukuran lebar 30 cm dan panjang 46 cm yang terletak pada mihrab masjid. Peletakan batu pertama menggunakan batu dari Baitul Maqdis di Palestina, oleh karena itu masjid ini kemudian dinamakan Masjid Al Aqsha.

#Wikipedia
textTranslated:
The establishment of the Kudus Tower Mosque cannot be separated from the role of Sunan Kudus as the initiator and founder. Like other Walisongo, Sunan Kudus uses a cultural approach in preaching. He adapted and indigenized Islamic teachings in a society that already had an established culture influenced by Hinduism and Buddhism. The acculturation of Hindu and Buddhist culture in Islamic preaching carried out by Sunan Kudus is clearly visible in the architecture and building concept of the Kudus Tower Mosque.

This mosque was built in 956 AH or 1549 AD. This is based on Arabic inscriptions written on a stone stele measuring 30 cm wide and 46 cm long which is located on the mosque's mihrab. The first stone was laid using stones from Baitul Maqdis in Palestine, therefore this mosque was later called the Al Aqsa Mosque.

#Wikipedia
title: Masjid Al-Aqsha Menara Kudus

address: Jl. Menara, Pejaten, Langgardalem, Kec. Kota Kudus, Kabupaten Kudus, Jawa Tengah, Indonesia
name: Nova Ariyanto
text:
Situs ziarah kondang di Kudus. Rasanya tak ada yg tak kenal dg kompleks Masjid Menara Kudus. Selain sohor dg kompleks makam Sunan Kudus, masjid yg sudah berdiri lima abad silam ini pun sudah tergolong ke dalam bangunan cagar budaya.

Sejarah mencatat Masjid Menara Kudus dibangun oleh Sunan Kudus pada warsa 1549. Masjid ini mempunyai lima pintu dibagian sebelah kanan dan lima pintu bagian sebelah kiri. Jendelanya semuanya ada empat buah.

Pintu besar terdiri dari lima buah dan tiang besar di dalam masjid yang berasal dari kayu jati ada delapan buah. Di bagian dalam masjid terdapat kolam masjid, kolam yang disebut dengan padasan tersebut merupakan peninggalan kuno dan dijadikan sebagai tempat wudhu.

Ketika memasuki kedalam masjid, kalian akan melewati sebuah gapura berbentuk candi bentar disamping kanan dan kiri yang menghubungkan langsung dengan pagar keliling kompleks masjid. Selain itu juga, terdapat gapura berbentuk paduraksa yang terdapat di serambi masjid dan di halaman utama masjid.

Dulu gapura paduraksa mempunyai fungsi sebagai pintu masuk menuju halaman serambi dan halaman utama masjid. Namun, keberadaanya sekarang ditutup dan tidak berfungsi seperti dahulu. Karena adanya perluasan Masjid Menara Kudus pada tahun 1933.

Tak seperti lazimnya masjid di Jawa, arsitektur Masjid Menara Kudus terbilang unik yakni dg keberadaan sebuah menara. Menara ini dibuat dari batu bata merah yang dibuat dengan menggunakan teknik kosod. Kemudian di bagian sisinya terdapat hiasan yang terbuat dari keramik cina.

Selanjutnya, diatas menara terdapat ruangan yang dapat dinaiki dengan tangga. Atap ruangan bangunan terbuat dari kayu dan terdapat beduk yang diikatkan dengan salah satu balok kayu atap. Sepintas Menara Kudus menyerupai candi dg bentuk kulkul yang ada di Bali.
textTranslated:
Famous pilgrimage site in Kudus. It seems like there is no one who is not familiar with the Kudus Tower Mosque complex. Apart from being famous for its Sunan Kudus tomb complex, this mosque, which was founded five centuries ago, is also classified as a cultural heritage building.

History records that the Kudus Tower Mosque was built by Sunan Kudus in 1549. This mosque has five doors on the right and five doors on the left. There are four windows in all.

The large door consists of five pieces and there are eight large pillars in the mosque made of teak wood. Inside the mosque there is a mosque pool, the pool called the padasan is an ancient relic and is used as a place for ablution.

When entering the mosque, you will pass through a gate in the shape of a momentary temple on the right and left which connects directly to the fence around the mosque complex. Apart from that, there is a paduraksa-shaped gate in the mosque foyer and in the main courtyard of the mosque.

In the past, the paduraksa gate functioned as an entrance to the foyer and main courtyard of the mosque. However, it is now closed and does not function as before. Due to the expansion of the Kudus Tower Mosque in 1933.

Unlike most mosques in Java, the architecture of the Kudus Tower Mosque is unique, namely the presence of a tower. The tower is made of red bricks made using the kosod technique. Then on the sides there are decorations made of Chinese ceramics.

Furthermore, above the tower there is a room that can be climbed by stairs. The roof of the building is made of wood and there is a drum attached to one of the wooden roof beams. At first glance, the Kudus Tower resembles a kulkul-shaped temple in Bali.

Area sholat wanita rada susah ya dicari klo emang gapernah sholat disitu, tpi tinggal ngikutin jalan samping masjidnya pas yg agak masuk2 kedalam ada tanda petunjuk jalannya kok. Untuk mukena sedia banyak, tmpat wudhu jga banyak, plus didepan pas ada toilet. Salah satu tempat yg aku betah ya di tmpat sholat ini, karena luas, adem, dan interiornya khas jawa. Apalgi klo sayup2 ada yg ngaji didalem duh..jadi tmbah damai rasanya.

Banyak kang foto bagi yg pengen diabadikan sama keluarga besar atau rombongan, ada jajan2nan juga, aksesoris, bahkan jenang. Rekomen buat destinasi ziarah 😊
textTranslated:
Favorite place when you're feeling down... because when you come here you feel calm and peaceful. Even though it's really hot outside during the day, it's cool inside.
There are lots of motorbike parking lots around the tower, from the side of the main road, or near the bookstore. There are also motorbike parking lots but you have to walk a little.

The women's prayer area is a bit difficult to find if you've never prayed there, but you just have to follow the road next to the mosque when you go inside and there are signs pointing the way. There are plenty of mukenas available, there are also lots of ablution places, plus there is a toilet in front of the building. One of the places I feel at home is this prayer place, because it is spacious, cool, and has a typical Javanese interior. What's more, if there's even someone reciting the Koran inside, it feels even more peaceful.

There are lots of photos for those who want to immortalize them with their extended family or group, there are also snacks, accessories, even jenang. Recommendations for a pilgrimage destination 😊

name: ningida
text:
Salah satu kompleks makam wali dengan desain arsitektur terbaik. Penikmat arsitektur pasti menyukai konsep area makam di sini. Untuk menuju lokasi pemerintah daerah membuat lokasi parkir bus agak jauh dari kompleks makam. Kemudian memberdayakan masyarakat sekitar untuk menyediakan odong-odong, becak dan dokar atau bendi. Dengan tiket masuk yang kita bayarkan kita bisa memilih untuk naik kendaraan-kendaraan tersebut free atau menambah beberapa belas ribu rupiah saja.

Turun dari transportasi umum, kita kan berjalan sedikit ke lokasi makam dan masjid. Tidak jauh. Sekitar satu sampai dua menit saja. Sampai di lokasi kita akan menjumpai gapura sekaligus menara kudus yang terkenal itu. Di kanan menara ada masjid modern, Al Aqsha, yang modern dan baru. Kompleks makam ada di sebelah kiri.

Sebelum masuk ke area makam disediakan tempat wudhlu terbuka yang tidak dibedakan antara jama'ah perempuan dan laki-laki. Jalur masuk dan keluar tidak dibedakan alias satu jalur. Jadi ketika jama'ah overload, akan crowded sekali. Ketika sepi nyaman-nyaman saja. Tidak disediakan tempat khusus untuk sandal. Jadi pengunjung banyak yang meletakkan sendalnya di depan pintu masuk.

Kompleks makamnya luas dan berkonsep terbuka dengan banyak joglo-joglo. Jadi meskipun ramai udara masih nyaman. Di depan Masjid Menara Kudus banyak tersedia jasa foto langsung jadi. Foto dulu sebelum masuk ke lokasi dan ambil hasilnya ketika keluar dari lokasi. Jika membawa kamera atau handphone kita juga bisa sekalian minta difotokan.

Transportasi dari makam ke tempat parkir bus tidak termasuk dalam tiket  berangkat. Jadi kita harus mencari transportasi sendiri. Tersedia angkot yang bisa digunakan beramai-ramai. Dicarter satu angkot beramai-ramai.

Untuk oleh-oleh, Kudus terkenal dengan jenangnya. Salah satu yang terkenal adalaj Jenang Kudus Mubarok. Harganya cukup terjangkau. Dijual juga aneka jenang lainnya, baik dalam kemasan modern ataupun dalam baskom-baskom khas jaman dulu. Belanja oleh-oleh di sini cukup menyenangkan. Murah, enak dan banyak pilihan.
textTranslated:
One of the guardian tomb complexes with the best architectural design. Architecture lovers will definitely like the concept of the tomb area here. To get to the location, the local government has made a bus parking location some distance from the tomb complex. Then empower the local community to provide odong-odong, pedicabs and dokars or hansoms. With the entrance ticket that we pay, we can choose to ride these vehicles for free or add just a few thousand rupiah.

Getting off public transportation, we walk a little to the location of the grave and mosque. Not far. Only about one to two minutes. Arriving at the location, we will find the gate and the famous holy tower. To the right of the minaret is a modern mosque, Al Aqsa, which is modern and new. The tomb complex is on the left.

Before entering the tomb area, an open ablution area is provided which does not differentiate between male and female worshipers. The entry and exit routes are not differentiated, i.e. one route. So when the congregation is overloaded, it will be very crowded. When it's quiet, it's just comfortable. There is no special place for sandals. So many visitors put their sandals in front of the entrance.

The tomb complex is spacious and has an open concept with many joglos. So even though it's crowded, the air is still comfortable. In front of the Kudus Tower Mosque, there are many instant photo services available. Take photos before entering the location and take the results when you leave the location. If you bring a camera or cellphone, you can also ask to have your photo taken.

Transportation from the cemetery to the bus park is not included in the departure ticket. So we have to find our own transportation. Public transportation is available that can be used by groups of people. A crowd chartered a public transportation.

For souvenirs, Kudus is famous for its jenang. One of the famous ones is Jenang Kudus Mubarok. The price is quite affordable. Various other types of jenang are also sold, both in modern packaging and in typical old-fashioned basins. Shopping for souvenirs here is quite fun. Cheap, delicious and lots of choices.

ALAQSO MOSQUE
Or better known as the HOLY MENARA mosque, which is located in the city
Kudus, Central Java, Indonesia, is a very historic mosque for Muslims, especially in Java. Because it is closely related to the period of the spread of Islamic teachings spread by the saints and Sunan, namely SUNAN KUDUS. This mosque was built by Sunan Kudus and at the same time became a center for religious propagation activities. Islam in that area.
Apart from that, around the mosque are the graves of Sunan Kudus and his family. Even after his death, his services are still remembered and he can still contribute to developing the economy of the holy community because every day this maqom and mosque are always crowded with pilgrims from all over Indonesia.

text:
Bersilaturahmi di rumah sodara dekat masjid Al Aqsha menara kudus, lalu diajak sekalian melihat masjidnya dan berziarah. Alhamdulillah bisa berada di masjid menara kudus yang sangat bersejarah.

Masjid Menara Kudus adalah salah satu tempat suci bagi umat Muslim yang berada di kota Kudus, Provinsi Jawa Tengah, Indonesia. Masjid ini terkenal dengan menara bersejarahnya yang dikenal sebagai Menara Kudus. Menara ini memiliki ketinggian sekitar 50 meter dan menjadi simbol kota Kudus.

Menara Kudus sendiri memiliki arsitektur yang unik dan menarik. Menara ini memiliki 3 lantai dengan bentuk persegi empat dan di atasnya terdapat sebuah kubah setengah bola. Selain itu, Menara Kudus juga memiliki ukiran-ukiran yang indah dengan gaya seni Islam khas Nusantara.

Masjid Menara Kudus sendiri memiliki sejarah yang panjang. Masjid ini dibangun pada abad ke-16 oleh Sunan Kudus, salah satu wali Songo yang terkenal di Indonesia. Masjid ini menjadi pusat kegiatan keagamaan dan kebudayaan di kota Kudus dan sekitarnya. Selain itu, Masjid Menara Kudus juga menjadi tempat yang penting dalam perkembangan Islam di Indonesia.

Kini, Masjid Menara Kudus telah menjadi tempat ziarah bagi umat Muslim dari berbagai daerah di Indonesia maupun dari luar negeri. Masjid ini menjadi bukti keberagaman budaya Islam di Indonesia yang diwariskan dari masa lalu dan masih dijaga dengan baik hingga saat ini.
textTranslated:
Visited at your friend's house near the Al Aqsa mosque, the holy tower, then were invited to see the mosque and make a pilgrimage. Thank God I was able to be in the very historic Kudus Minaret Mosque.

The Kudus Tower Mosque is one of the holy places for Muslims in the city of Kudus, Central Java Province, Indonesia. This mosque is famous for its historic tower known as the Kudus Tower. This tower has a height of around 50 meters and is a symbol of the city of Kudus.

Kudus Tower itself has unique and interesting architecture. This tower has 3 floors with a rectangular shape and on top there is a hemispherical dome. Apart from that, the Kudus Tower also has beautiful carvings in a typical Indonesian Islamic art style.

The Kudus Tower Mosque itself has a long history. This mosque was built in the 16th century by Sunan Kudus, one of the famous Songo saints in Indonesia. This mosque is the center of religious and cultural activities in the city of Kudus and its surroundings. Apart from that, the Kudus Tower Mosque is also an important place in the development of Islam in Indonesia.

Now, the Kudus Tower Mosque has become a place of pilgrimage for Muslims from various regions in Indonesia and abroad. This mosque is proof of the diversity of Islamic culture in Indonesia which was inherited from the past and is still well maintained today.
title: Masjid Al-Aqsha Menara Kudus

textTranslated:
Because I went there on Friday and it was close to Friday prayer time, I couldn't really explore inside the mosque, I could only look around the front yard of the Kanjeng Sunan Kudus Tomb and take photos in front of the icon of the Kudus Mosque 😊

The place for pilgrimage wasn't closed for long when we went there because it was nearing the time for Friday prayers

What's a bit difficult is finding a parking place because the Kudus Mosque area is in a small alley, so if you take a car you can't get inside there, but the one across the alley is mostly used as an impromptu parking lot, hehe
BTW, be careful if you want to cross the road to the mosque area because the road is very busy with vehicles passing by.

There is no entrance ticket, it's free
In the mosque alley, there are also lots of shops and street vendors selling all kinds of food, snacks, drinks and even Muslim clothing, the prices are affordable and varied.

Come visit the Al-Aqsa Kudus Mosque, worship and make a pilgrimage to the tomb of Sunan Kudus and do religious tourism there, hopefully we can increase our knowledge about Islam and our faith 😊

text:
Masjid ini berada satu kompleks dengan makam Sunan Kudus. Tetenger yang sangat ikonik adalah bangunan menaranya. Dibuat dari batu bata merah dengan bentuk yang menyerupai bangunan candi dan dihiasi keramik indah dari China. Sungguh perpaduan budaya yang menyuguhkan keindahan.

Tentunya masjid ini sebagai bukti sejarah yang agung, kaitannya dengan akulturasi budaya yang bersinergis. Ini membuktikan bahwa Islam itu sangat toleran terhadap budaya lokal dengan tanpa mengorbankan aspek tauhid. Hal itu sekaligus sebagai bukti bahwa Islam di tanah Jawa disebarkan secara damai, tanpa ada peperangan maupun paksaan. Tanpa ada pengrusakan maupun penghancuran budaya lama. Tetapi diajak secara persuasif untuk berislam.
textTranslated:
This mosque is in the same complex as the tomb of Sunan Kudus. The most iconic landmark is the tower building. Made of red brick with a shape that resembles a temple building and decorated with beautiful ceramics from China. What a blend of cultures that presents beauty.

Of course, this mosque is proof of great history, related to synergistic cultural acculturation. This proves that Islam is very tolerant of local culture without sacrificing aspects of monotheism. This is also proof that Islam in Java was spread peacefully, without any war or coercion. Without any destruction or destruction of old culture. But they were persuasively invited to convert to Islam.

address: Jl. Menara, Pejaten, Langgardalem, Kec. Kota Kudus, Kabupaten Kudus, Jawa Tengah, Indonesia
name: Handjuang Beureum
text:
Menara Kudus ini sangat unik bentuknya sama sekali tidak mirip dengan menara masjid pada umumnya, malah lebih menyerupai candi. Tapi jika diperhatikan dari sejarahnya, hal itu tentu saja tidak akan mengherankan karena bentuk Menara Kudus merupakan perpaduan budaya Hindu dan Islam. Seolah menjadi lambang proses masuknya agama Islam ke daerah ini yang tidak menimbulkan kekerasan, namun malah terbuka terhadap unsur-unsur kebudayaan lama di daerah setempat.
Bentuknya sederhana, terbuat dari tumpukan bata merah tanpa semen sebagai perekat, namun terlihat anggun dalam kekokohannya seolah tidak habis dimakan usia. Menara ini memiliki tinggi 17 meter, dengan luas sekitar 100 meter persegi, Atap menara merupakan konstruksi kayu jati yang membentuk semacam kubah yang menjadi tempat mengumandangkan azan.
Ketika bulan Ramadan, nuansa islami akan semakin terasa di tempat ini. Suara lembut pelantun ayat-ayat Al-Quran akan sering terdengar di antara hiruk pikuk pedagang oleh-oleh yang juga bernuansa islami.
Obyek wisata Menara Kudus terletak di Kelurahan Kauman, Kabupaten Kudus, Jawa Tengah. Berada sekitar 40 kilometer di sebelah timur Kota Semarang, bisa ditempuh dalam waktu kurang lebih satu setengah jam dengan menggunakan kendaraan bermotor. Di dekat menara, terdapat Masjid Kudus yang juga menjadi tujuan para peziarah atau wisatawan.
textTranslated:
The Kudus Tower is very unique in shape, not at all similar to mosque towers in general, in fact it looks more like a temple. But if you look at its history, this of course will not be surprising because the shape of the Kudus Tower is a combination of Hindu and Islamic cultures. It seems to be a symbol of the process of the entry of Islam into this area which did not cause violence, but instead opened up to elements of the old culture in the local area.
The shape is simple, made from a pile of red bricks without cement as an adhesive, but looks elegant in its sturdiness as if it has not worn out with age. This tower is 17 meters high, with an area of ​​around 100 square meters. The roof of the tower is a teak wood construction that forms a kind of dome from which the call to prayer is made.
During the month of Ramadan, the Islamic feel will be increasingly felt in this place. The gentle voice of someone singing verses from the Koran can often be heard amidst the hustle and bustle of souvenir sellers who also have Islamic nuances.
The Kudus Tower tourist attraction is located in Kauman Village, Kudus Regency, Central Java. Located about 40 kilometers east of Semarang City, it can be reached in approximately one and a half hours by motor vehicle. Near the tower, there is the Holy Mosque which is also a destination for pilgrims or tourists.
title: Masjid Al-Aqsha Menara Kudus

text:
Masjid Menara Kudus adalah salah satu masjid yang berperan dalam sejarah perkembangan Islam di Indonesia, khususnya di Jawa. Masjid yang berada di Kudus, Jawa Tengah, ini memiliki arsitektur unik, yakni perpaduan Hindu-Jawa dengan Islam.
Masjid bersejarah yang juga disebut dengan Masjid Al Aqsha dan Masjid Al Manar ini sudah eksis ada sejak tahun 1549. Letaknya berlokasi di Kecamatan Kauman, Kota Kudus, Jawa Tengah. Pendiri Masjid Kudus adalah Sunan Kudus atau Syekh Ja'far Shodiq.
textTranslated:
The Kudus Tower Mosque is one of the mosques that played a role in the history of the development of Islam in Indonesia, especially in Java. This mosque, which is located in Kudus, Central Java, has unique architecture, namely a combination of Hindu-Javanese and Islam.
This historic mosque, which is also called the Al Aqsa Mosque and Al Manar Mosque, has existed since 1549. It is located in Kauman District, Kudus City, Central Java. The founder of the Kudus Mosque is Sunan Kudus or Sheikh Ja'far Shodiq.
title: Masjid Al-Aqsha Menara Kudus

textTranslated: Menara Kudus Mosque (official name: Al-Aqsa Manarat Qudus Mosque; mosque ID: 01.5.14.19.02.000001[1] Javanese: Hanacaraka: ꦩꦱ꧀ꦗꦶꦢ꧀​ꦩꦼꦤꦫ​ꦏꦸꦢꦸꦱ꧀ ​​Pegon and standard Arabic: مسجد م نارة قدوس) is an ancient mosque built by Sunan Holy since 1549 AD (956 Hijriah). The current location is in Kauman Village, Kota District, Kudus Regency, Central Java. This mosque is unique because it has a tower that is similar to a temple building and an architectural pattern that combines Islamic cultural concepts with Hindu-Buddhist culture, thus showing the process of acculturation in Javanese Islam.
title: Masjid Al-Aqsha Menara Kudus

address: Jl. Menara, Pejaten, Langgardalem, Kec. Kota Kudus, Kabupaten Kudus, Jawa Tengah, Indonesia

text:
Masjid Menara Kudus ..
Merupakan ikon utama kota kudus yang masih terjaga dan dijaga kelestariannya dari dulu sampai sekarang , termasuk di dalamnya ada Maqom Waliyulloh "Syekh Jafar Shodiq" yang bergelar sebagai SUNAN KUDUS ,
Untuk maqomnya sendiri buka hingga jam 12 malam dan diatas jam 12 tutup selanjutnya buka kembali setelah adzan subuh .
Tetapi utk masjidnya disini tetap terbuka 24 jam

tempatnya bersih dan tempat parkir sepeda motor luas karena sudah disediakan gedung parkir khusus untuk peziarah yang menggunakan motor .

Untuk parkir mobil masi terbatas di pinggir jalan raya sunan kudus karena lahan parkir yg kurang bagi para peziarah, disekitaran masjid sini banyak menjual pernak pernik beraneka ragam oleh2 khas kudus serta berbagai kebutuhan untuk para peziarah terutama makanan ..

Selain itu lingkungan di sekitaran dlm masjid maupun di luar "bersih"  terbebas dari "pengemis" yang biasanya berseliweran di tempat2 ziarah seperti ini dan terkadang sering memaksa meminta sehingga mengganggu para peziarah ..
textTranslated:
Kudus Tower Mosque..
It is the main icon of the holy city which is still preserved and preserved from the past until now, including Maqom Waliyulloh "Sheikh Jafar Shodiq" who has the title SUNAN HOLY,
The maqom itself is open until 12 at night and after 12 it closes and then opens again after the morning call to prayer.
But the mosque here remains open 24 hours

The place is clean and the motorbike parking area is spacious because a special parking building has been provided for pilgrims using motorbikes.

Parking for cars is still limited on the side of Jalan Raya Sunan Kudus because there is not enough parking space for pilgrims. Around the mosque here there are many selling knick-knacks and various typical Kudus souvenirs as well as various necessities for pilgrims, especially food...

Apart from that, the environment inside the mosque and outside is "clean" free from "beggars" who usually mill about at pilgrimage places like this and sometimes forcefully ask, thus disturbing the pilgrims...

address: Jl. Menara, Pejaten, Langgardalem, Kec. Kota Kudus, Kabupaten Kudus, Jawa Tengah, Indonesia
name: Ali Akbar Nafiz
text:
Masjid Menara Kudus merupakan salah satu peninggalan sejarah, sebagai bukti proses penyebaran Islam di Tanah Jawa. Masjid ini tergolong unik karena desain bangunannya, yang merupakan penggabungan antara Budaya Hindu dan Budaya Islam. Sebagaimana kita ketahui, sebelum Islam, Di Jawa telah berkembang agama Budha dan Hindu dengan peninggalannya berupa Candi dan Pura. Selain itu ada penyembahan terhadap Roh Nenek Moyang (Animisme) dan kepercayaan terhadap benda-benda (Dinamisme). Masjid Menara Kudus menjadi bukti, bagaimana sebuah perpaduan antara Kebudayaan Islam dan Kebudayaan Hindu telah menghasilkan sebuah bangunan yang tergolong unik dan bergaya arsitektur tinggi. Sebuah bangunan masjid, namun dengan menara dalam bentuk candi dan berbagai ornamen lain yang bergaya Hindu.

Menurut sejarah, Masjid Menara Kudus didirikan oleh Sunan Kudus atau Ja’far Shodiq ialah putera dari R.Usman Haji yang bergelar dengan Sunan Ngudung di Jipang Panolan (ada yang mengatakan tempat tersebut terletak di sebelah utara Blora). Sunan Kudus kawin dengan Dewi Rukhil, puteri dari R.Makdum Ibrahim, Kanjeng Sunan Bonan di Tuban. R.Makdum Ibrahim adalah putera R.Rachmad (Sunan Ampel) putera Maulana Ibrahim. Dengan demikian Sunan Kudus adalah menantunya Kanjeng Sunan Bonang. Sunan Kudus selain dikenal seorang ahli agama juga dikenal sebagai ahli ilmu tauhid, ilmu hadist dan ilmu fiqh. Karena itu, diantara kesembilan wali, hanya beliau yang terkenal sebagai “Waliyil Ilmi”. Adapun cara Sunan Kudus menyebarkan agama Islam adalah dengan jalan kebijaksanaan, sehingga mendapat simpati dari penduduk yang saat itu masih memeluk agama Hindu. Salah satu contohnya adalah, Sapi merupakan hewan yang sangat dihormati oleh agama Hindu, suatu ketika kanjeng Sunan mengikat sapi di pekarangan masjid, setelah mereka datang Kanjeng Sunan bertabligh, sehingga diantara mereka banyak yang memeluk Islam. Dan sampai sekarang pun di wilayah Kudus, khususnya Kudus Kulon dilarang menyembelih sapi sebagai penghormatan terhadap agama Hindu sampai dengan saat ini.
textTranslated:
Menara Kudus Mosque is one of the historical relics, as evidence of the process of spreading Islam in Java. This mosque is unique because of its building design, which is a fusion between Hindu Culture and Islamic Culture. As we know, before Islam, Buddhism and Hinduism developed in Java with their remains in the form of temples and temples. In addition there is the worship of Ancestor Spirits (Animism) and belief in things (Dynamism). Menara Kudus Mosque is evidence of how a fusion between Islamic Culture and Hindu Culture has produced a building that is unique and stylish in high architecture. A mosque building, but with a minaret in the form of a temple and various other ornaments that are Hindu in style.

According to history, Menara Kudus Mosque was founded by Sunan Kudus or Ja'far Shodiq, the son of R.Usman Haji who had the title of Sunan Ngudung in Jipang Panolan (some say the place is located on the north side of Blora). Sunan Kudus married Dewi Rukhil, daughter of R. Makdum Ibrahim, Kanjeng Sunan Bonan in Tuban. R. Makdum Ibrahim is the son of R. Rachmad (Sunan Ampel) the son of Maulana Ibrahim. Thus Sunan Kudus is the son-in-law of Kanjeng Sunan Bonang. Sunan Kudus, in addition to being known as a religious expert, is also known as an expert in monotheism, hadith and jurisprudence. Because of that, among the nine guardians, only he is known as "Waliyil Ilmi". As for the way Sunan Kudus spread Islam was through the path of wisdom, so that he got sympathy from the people who at that time still embraced Hinduism. One of the examples is, Cow is an animal that is highly respected by Hinduism, once Kanjeng Sunan tied a cow in the mosque grounds, after they came Kanjeng Sunan preached, so many of them embraced Islam. And even now in the Kudus region, especially Kudus Kulon, it is forbidden to slaughter cows as a tribute to the Hindu religion until now.
title: Masjid Al-Aqsha Menara Kudus

address: Jl. Menara, Pejaten, Langgardalem, Kec. Kota Kudus, Kabupaten Kudus, Jawa Tengah, Indonesia
name: Aya Chan (Aya)
text: Alhamdulillah... Alhamdulillah... Alhamdulillah..  Masjid Al Aqsha Kota Kudus ini merupakan salah satu bangunan tempat ibadah bagi umat Islam yang bersejarah. Yup... Masjid ini berkaitan dengan wali songo.... Bagi umat agama Islam tentu tidak asing dengan nama wali songo ( Bahasa Jawa ). Nah.. nah.. nah, apa kaitannya antara Masjid Al Aqsha Kudus ini dengan Wali Songo? Hmmm... Konon di bangunan Masjid ini, Salah seorang wali songo yaitu sunan kudus melaksanakan sholat, mengaji, dakwah dan aktivitas ibadah lainnya, disini, di masjid Al Aqsha ini... Bertujuan untuk mengenalkan dan menyebarkan agama islam di kota kudus.  Mengingat waktu itu mayoritas masyarakat pribumi memeluk dan menganut ajaran agam Hindu, Budha dan Kepercayaan Konghucu. Uniknya di masjid ini, muadzin bisa mengumandangkan adzan di menara... Bangunan menara ini terpisah tidak jauh dari bangunan Masjid. Bangunan menara menyerupai candi. Bangunan Menara ini sebagai bentuk toleransi umat beragama untuk menghormati agama Hindu. Begitu dear singkat ceritanya... Nah kalau kamu ingin lebih jelas lagi cerita tentang sejarah berdirinya masjid Al Aqsha ini, mending kamu datang kesini... :-)
textTranslated: Alhamdulillah... Alhamdulillah... Alhamdulillah.. The Al Aqsa Mosque in Kudus City is one of the historic buildings for places of worship for Muslims. Yup... This mosque is related to wali songo.... For Muslims, of course the name wali songo (Javanese) is familiar. Well.. well.. well, what is the connection between the Al Aqsa Kudus Mosque and Wali Songo? Hmmm... It is said that in this mosque building, one of the songo saints, namely Sunan Kudus, carries out prayers, reciting the Koran, preaching and other worship activities, here, at the Al Aqsa mosque... The aim is to introduce and spread the Islamic religion in the holy city.  Remembering that at that time the majority of indigenous people embraced and adhered to the teachings of Hinduism, Buddhism and Confucianism. Uniquely in this mosque, the muezzin can give the call to prayer in the tower... The tower building is separate not far from the mosque building. The tower building resembles a temple. This tower building is a form of religious tolerance to respect Hinduism. So, dear, short story... Well, if you want a clearer story about the history of the establishment of the Al Aqsa mosque, it's better for you to come here... :-)

text:
Asli, ini pengalaman ku yang tidak ku terlupakan. sebelumnya, aku belum pernah ziarah dari kecil sampai gede. Jadi aku gak tau ziarah itu gimana, aku tiba2 diajak sm temenku ke menara kudus. Pas aku search liat di ig kayak tempat wisata, jadi yaudah aku pakai outfit main kayak biasa (jaket crop top, manset item, celana) pas nyampe sana masih belum sadar kalo itu ziarah makam Sunan Kudus. Pas nyampe sana, disuruh wudu, aku udah hah? Karna gatau ngikut aja😭 abis itu suruh nyopot sendal masuk ke dalem, kanan kiri kuburan semua, aku hah lagi? Kok kuburan semua😭😭 ... Terus pada pake peci sama gamisan semua.. terus aku ngikut  temenku aja.. Duduk di gazebo..Kok pada baca2.. aku ikut2an aja
( aku baca  Al Fatihah sm Al iklas)  bisaku baca itu.. Setelah itu aku doa hajat ku🙏  abis itu pulang, itu pertama kalinya aku ngerasain ziarah, MasyaAllah. Makasih temenku akhirnya diumur 24th ini pertama kalinya aku ziarah, Next time semoga bisa ziarah lagi, seneng bgt aku❤❤
textTranslated:
Honestly, this is an experience I will never forget. Previously, I had never made a pilgrimage from childhood to adulthood. So I didn't know what a pilgrimage was like, I was suddenly invited by my friend to the holy tower. When I searched, I saw on IG that it looked like a tourist spot, so I put on my usual playing outfit (crop top jacket, cuff items, trousers) when I got there, I still didn't realize that it was a pilgrimage to the Sunan Kudus grave. When I got there, I was told to perform ablution, I was done, huh? Because I don't know how to follow 😭 after that I was told to take off my sandals and go inside, left and right, all the graves, me huh again? Why are they all graves😭😭... Then everyone is wearing caps and gamis... then I'm just following my friends... Sitting in the gazebo... How come I'm reading... I'm just going along
(I read Al Fatihah and Al Iklas) I can read that... After that I prayed my hajat🙏 then went home, that was the first time I felt like a pilgrimage, MashaAllah. Thank you my friend, finally at the age of 24 this is the first time I have made a pilgrimage, next time I hope I can make a pilgrimage again, I'm really happy❤❤

In front of the mosque, many people sell typical Kudus jenang. And there are photo services that can be done immediately.

text:
Masjid Al-Aqsha Menara Kudus merupakan ikon dari Kota Kudus. Terletak di pusat kota dengan pengunjung yang ramai tiap harinya terutama para Perayaan Hari Besar Islam. Di barat masjid terdapat pesarean yang mana Kanjeng Ja'far Shodiq (Sunan Kudus) dimakamkan disini, tak ayal banyak peziarah maupun pecinta sejarah berziarah ke makam pencetus nama kota Kudus.
Lingkungan kawasan menara kudus terbilang cukup bersih dan para pedagangnya tertata rapi walaupun masih terdapat sampah berserakan di sepanjang jalan menuju gerbang masuk masjid.
textTranslated:
The Al-Aqsa Menara Kudus Mosque is an icon of the Holy City. Located in the city center with lots of visitors every day, especially during Islamic Holiday Celebrations. To the west of the mosque there is a pesarean where Kanjeng Ja'far Shodiq (Sunan Kudus) is buried here, no wonder many pilgrims and history lovers make the pilgrimage to the grave of the originator of the name Kudus city.
The environment of the holy tower area is quite clean and the traders are neatly arranged, although there is still rubbish strewn along the road leading to the mosque entrance gate.
title: Masjid Al-Aqsha Menara Kudus

textTranslated: When you go on a pilgrimage to this place, it feels very different from when you go on a pilgrimage to other places. The location is very clean and neat, so elegantly arranged, it feels like we are visiting our grandparents' house because it is so familiar (perhaps because there are many buildings with traditional Javanese lights and ornaments). Coincidentally, when we arrived at this place, it was already evening, so the lights that were on also added to the serene atmosphere of this place. Unfortunately, we didn't have time to take pictures inside the tomb complex because when we entered there were so many pilgrims.

name: DUDU KOPI IN'sPIRASI
text:
Masjid Al Aqsha Kudus atau masjid menara merupakan bangunan masjid yang memadupadankan arsitektur islam-hindu. Disebut juga sebagai masjid menara karena ciri khas yang ada pada bangunan menaranya yang sperti bangunan candi Hindu.

Lokasinya tepat di pusat kota Kudus, sekitar 2 km dari simpang 7 Kudus. Di lokasi ini terdapat kompleks pemakaman yang biasa dikunjungi oleh para peziarah. Terdapat salah satu makam Walisongo, yakni Sunan Kudus yang berjasa besar dalam penyebaran agama Islam di pulau Jawa terutama di kabupaten Kudus.

Disekitar kompleks masjid terdapat banyak toko yang menawarkan cindera mata Dan jajanan khas kabupaten Kudus. Selama pandemi wajib mematuhi protokol kesehatan, jangan lupa masker dan handsanitizer.

Selamat berziarah, selamat berlibur jaga kesehatan..😁😁😁
textTranslated:
The Al Aqsa Kudus Mosque or minaret mosque is a mosque building that combines Islamic-Hindu architecture. It is also called a minaret mosque because of the distinctive characteristics of the minaret building, which is like a Hindu temple building.

The location is right in the center of Kudus city, about 2 km from Simpang 7 Kudus. At this location there is a burial complex which is usually visited by pilgrims. There is one of the graves of Walisongo, namely Sunan Kudus, who made a big contribution to the spread of Islam on the island of Java, especially in Kudus district.

Around the mosque complex there are many shops offering souvenirs and typical snacks from Kudus district. During the pandemic, you must comply with health protocols, don't forget your mask and hand sanitizer.

Happy pilgrimage, happy holiday, take care of your health..😁😁😁
title: Masjid Al-Aqsha Menara Kudus
